00:02:02,182 --> 00:02:05,151
''Some will tell you...
some will hide it''

6
00:02:11,191 --> 00:02:14,160
''lt's a strange situation
to be in''

7
00:02:45,225 --> 00:02:48,194
''How long will anyone
travel through a lonely journey?''

8
00:02:56,236 --> 00:02:59,205
''How long will anyone
spend a lifetime in loneliness''

9
00:03:08,248 --> 00:03:11,217
''She will come some day...
my love will''

10
00:03:18,258 --> 00:03:20,226
''How long will l remain lonely?''

11
00:03:28,268 --> 00:03:30,236
''How long will you remain lonely?''

12
00:03:40,280 --> 00:03:42,248
''He will surely come some day...''

13
00:03:45,285 --> 00:03:47,253
''My love, will''

14
00:03:50,290 --> 00:03:52,258
''Somewhere, someday...''

15
00:03:54,294 --> 00:03:56,262
''you and l will meet''

16
00:03:59,299 --> 00:04:02,268
''Every man dreams of the
girl he wants''

17
00:04:43,343 --> 00:04:44,310
''Love...''

18
00:04:45,345 --> 00:04:46,312
''l'll fall in love''

19
00:04:48,348 --> 00:04:50,316
''Mischief, l will be up to too''

20
00:04:52,352 --> 00:04:54,320
''She's the one l dream about.
She's the one l desire''

21
00:04:56,356 --> 00:04:58,324
''Every moment, l wait for her...''

22
00:05:01,361 --> 00:05:03,329
''She's the one l pine for''

23
00:05:04,364 --> 00:05:07,333
''He'll come with
the bridal headgear...''

24
00:05:08,368 --> 00:05:11,337
''the bridal procession,
he will lead''

25
00:05:12,372 --> 00:05:14,340
''He'll take me away as his bride''

26
00:05:20,380 --> 00:05:23,349
''Every girl dreams of the
boy she desires''

27
00:05:28,388 --> 00:05:31,357
''Every man dreams of the
woman he desires''

28
00:05:38,398 --> 00:05:41,367
''Some will tell you...
some will hide it''

29
00:05:44,404 --> 00:05:47,373
''lt's a strange situation
to be in''

30
00:06:28,448 --> 00:06:30,416
Praise Lord Shankar

31
00:06:34,454 --> 00:06:36,422
You're Shiv. And l'm Shiv too

32
00:06:37,457 --> 00:06:39,425
But you're God.
And l'm an ordinary human being

33
00:06:40,460 --> 00:06:43,429
Lord, l'm starting a new life today.
You must've seen the newspaper.

34
00:06:45,465 --> 00:06:47,433
l wonder how many people saw
that ad on the second page

35
00:06:48,468 --> 00:06:51,437
They want an Executive Manager.
One post, many aspirants

36
00:06:53,473 --> 00:06:55,441
But make sure You bless only me

37
00:06:57,477 --> 00:07:00,446
Lord, when will this devotee of Yours
find a job? When will l make money?

38
00:07:01,481 --> 00:07:04,450
When will l have a wife and kids?
When will l tell stories to them?

39
00:07:06,486 --> 00:07:09,455
Our little family will then
come here and sing praises to You

40
00:07:11,491 --> 00:07:12,458
Praise Lord Shankar

41
00:07:13,493 --> 00:07:15,461
Just get me this job, Lord... please

42
00:07:17,497 --> 00:07:19,465
And don't You think
of anyone else. Okay?

43
00:07:21,501 --> 00:07:24,470
No matter how much
anyone prays to You

44
00:07:27,507 --> 00:07:28,474
My obesiences, Goddess Parvati

45
00:07:29,509 --> 00:07:30,476
l will say nothing to Shivji.
He won't listen to anything

46
00:07:35,515 --> 00:07:38,484
A woman has to struggle so much
in a man's world

47
00:07:40,520 --> 00:07:43,489
We've got to get pushed around
so much, try so many tricks to make it

48
00:07:46,526 --> 00:07:48,494
Now for today's headlines

49
00:07:49,529 --> 00:07:51,497
Look at the speeches they make

50
00:07:52,532 --> 00:07:55,501
And women would have said the
same things with so much of compassion

51
00:07:56,536 --> 00:07:58,504
But some people just won't listen

52
00:08:01,541 --> 00:08:04,510
Let's see the second page.
Maybe l'll find some justice here

53
00:08:09,549 --> 00:08:12,518
A job! There is a vacancy!
For the post of Executive Manager!

54
00:08:15,555 --> 00:08:18,524
''Gender, no bar! The same status
for both, men and women''

55
00:08:20,560 --> 00:08:23,529
l could make it. l'm so qualified...
l just can't lose out.

56
00:08:27,567 --> 00:08:30,536
But You know who will be
the obstacle. Men again!

57
00:08:33,573 --> 00:08:34,574
lt's up to You now, O Goddess

58
00:08:34,574 --> 00:08:35,541
Please accept my humble plea

59
00:08:36,576 --> 00:08:37,543
And please get me this job

60
00:08:39,579 --> 00:08:42,548
You must win, Goddess.
Not Shivji. At least not this time

61
00:09:13,613 --> 00:09:15,581
Going to eat? Go on

62
00:09:23,623 --> 00:09:24,590
Will you have some water?
- No

63
00:09:25,625 --> 00:09:26,592
Tea?
- No

64
00:09:27,627 --> 00:09:28,628
A cigarette then?
- No

65
00:09:28,628 --> 00:09:29,595
Like to chew some tobacco?
- No

66
00:09:30,630 --> 00:09:32,598
How about meeting

67
00:09:37,637 --> 00:09:39,605
You have no vices.
You're going to get this job

68
00:09:40,640 --> 00:09:41,607
How come?
- True. This Hyderabadi...

69
00:09:43,643 --> 00:09:45,611
can understand what your heart says.
l've been doing it for years

70
00:09:47,647 --> 00:09:48,614
You're absolutely right, you know.

71
00:09:50,650 --> 00:09:52,618
l'm No 1 ! l have all the degrees
- Really?

72
00:09:54,654 --> 00:09:56,622
No power can stop you then

73
00:09:57,657 --> 00:10:00,626
l'm Dil-phenk Hyderabadi. You?
- My name... Shiv. Shiv Kapoor

74
00:10:04,664 --> 00:10:07,633
Shiv Kapoor? Do something, Pooja!
Or you're going to lose this job

75
00:10:09,669 --> 00:10:11,637
Think of something. Go on!

76
00:10:15,675 --> 00:10:17,643
What destiny! What luck, my boy!

77
00:10:22,682 --> 00:10:25,651
Don't you forget me.
- How can you say such a thing?

78
00:10:27,687 --> 00:10:29,655
As if l'd forget you! Don't worry.
- Dil-phenk, come here...

79
00:10:30,690 --> 00:10:33,659
and stop chatting. Come on.
- The gentleman is calling me

80
00:10:37,697 --> 00:10:38,664
He gives me great respect

81
00:10:40,700 --> 00:10:42,668
Don't you forget me
- Don't worry. Go on

82
00:11:01,721 --> 00:11:03,689
Who are you?
What are you here for?

83
00:11:05,725 --> 00:11:06,692
Sit down. Sit

84
00:11:08,728 --> 00:11:10,696
Okay, stand up....
Never mind. l'll sit down

85
00:11:13,733 --> 00:11:15,701
What's that in your hand?
- Certificates of my qualification

86
00:11:17,737 --> 00:11:19,705
For a job in Papa's office?
- Yes, well...

87
00:11:20,740 --> 00:11:23,709
they issued that ad in the newspapers
for the post of Executive Manager

88
00:11:26,746 --> 00:11:27,713
And so, l...

89
00:11:31,751 --> 00:11:33,719
Why? What happened?
- This morning at breakfast...

90
00:11:35,755 --> 00:11:39,714
Papa received a call from a
very influential man

91
00:11:40,760 --> 00:11:42,728
Your job is gone.
- Gone? How can that be?

92
00:11:44,764 --> 00:11:47,733
He receives a call and l lose my job?
Where is your Papa?

93
00:11:48,768 --> 00:11:49,735
Calm down... sit

94
00:11:52,772 --> 00:11:54,740
You want to go very far
in life, don't you?

95
00:11:55,775 --> 00:11:58,744
All right then, trust Papa's daughter
and please go away. Okay?

96
00:12:01,781 --> 00:12:04,750
You're such a rich man's daughter
and yet, so compassionate

97
00:12:16,796 --> 00:12:18,764
Only my name won't impress him.
You must show him l'm capable too

98
00:12:20,800 --> 00:12:22,768
Only then will he agree.
... when should l meet you again?

99
00:12:23,803 --> 00:12:26,772
You don't have to meet me.
l'll meet up with you

100
00:12:28,808 --> 00:12:30,776
l have your name and address, right?
- Right

101
00:12:31,811 --> 00:12:33,779
So please leave now. Or l won't be
able to help you. Go on!

102
00:12:35,815 --> 00:12:37,783
What is it now?
- You haven't told me your name

103
00:12:42,822 --> 00:12:44,790
Beautiful name.
My name is Shiv Kapoor

104
00:12:52,832 --> 00:12:53,799
Please don't forget

105
00:12:59,839 --> 00:13:00,806
Damn it!

106
00:13:01,841 --> 00:13:04,810
Thanks for living up
to Delhi's reputation

107
00:13:05,845 --> 00:13:07,813
You've rammed into my
beautiful car, haven't you?

108
00:13:08,848 --> 00:13:10,816
Your beautiful sister has
rammed into your beautiful car!

109
00:13:11,851 --> 00:13:12,818
Brother! l've found a job!
- Great news!

110
00:13:13,853 --> 00:13:14,820
Which means...

111
00:13:16,856 --> 00:13:19,825
keeping me up all night with you
has finally helped!

112
00:13:22,862 --> 00:13:24,830
l can now personally shoulder
my responsibilities

113
00:13:26,866 --> 00:13:29,835
Here you are. Keep the change
and just get lost!

114
00:13:33,873 --> 00:13:35,841
Great affection brother and sister
are showering on each other!

115
00:13:37,877 --> 00:13:39,845
l'll give you news that will
brighten up your mood too, sis-in-law

116
00:13:40,880 --> 00:13:42,848
Come on, brother. Let's tell her

117
00:13:48,888 --> 00:13:50,856
Great news, sis!
- Sis? My foot!

118
00:13:55,895 --> 00:13:57,863
Sister-in-law!
- Let go! What are you doing?

119
00:14:05,905 --> 00:14:07,873
He's already panting.
- He's panting out of happiness

120
00:14:10,910 --> 00:14:12,878
l've got a job as Executive Manager.
- Thank God!

121
00:14:13,913 --> 00:14:15,881
You'll stand on your own two feet.
- Here l am. On my feet!

122
00:14:16,916 --> 00:14:18,884
You must stand up too.
- What for?

123
00:14:20,920 --> 00:14:22,888
For not having to cook tonight.
l'm treating you to dinner

124
00:14:23,923 --> 00:14:25,891
Where?
- At Delhi's Number One restaurant

125
00:14:47,947 --> 00:14:50,916
Wow! Do we get to eat like this every
day, or is this a one-time treat?

126
00:14:51,951 --> 00:14:54,920
My sister has a large heart, Kittu.
She would do so much for us.

127
00:14:56,956 --> 00:14:59,925
That's okay. But Pooja hasn't told us
how she got such a big job so easily

128
00:15:01,961 --> 00:15:03,929
Want me to tell you the truth?
Or just fib?

129
00:15:04,964 --> 00:15:06,932
You're always fibbing.
So tell us the truth this time

130
00:15:07,967 --> 00:15:09,935
Very well then. Here goes.
When l got there...

131
00:15:10,970 --> 00:15:12,938
it was as if all the doors
were open for me

132
00:15:15,975 --> 00:15:17,943
There were many Toms, Dicks
and Harrys before l got there...

133
00:15:18,978 --> 00:15:20,946
but who could have possessed
my kind of personality?

134
00:15:21,981 --> 00:15:23,949
Oh yes.
- When l moved further...

135
00:15:24,984 --> 00:15:26,952
the staff were so impressed,
they got up to salute me

136
00:15:27,987 --> 00:15:29,955
They rolled out the red carpet
for me, leading to the boss

137
00:15:31,991 --> 00:15:33,959
Guess what the boss said,
when he saw me?

138
00:15:34,994 --> 00:15:35,961
Go on.
- He said, ''My child'' !

139
00:15:37,997 --> 00:15:40,966
Such abilities, talent, confidence
and personality? ln this nation?

140
00:15:42,001 --> 00:15:43,969
''Where were you all
these days, my child?''

141
00:15:45,004 --> 00:15:46,972
You ought to have told him
that you were with us

142
00:15:49,008 --> 00:15:50,976
Pooja, the boss called you ''child'' ?
- Oh yes, brother

143
00:15:54,013 --> 00:15:55,981
And l started calling him ''Papa'' too

144
00:15:59,018 --> 00:16:00,986
l'm sure it's divine intervention.
- Oh yes

145
00:16:03,022 --> 00:16:04,990
All thanks to Goddess Parvati.
l wonder how She got Shivji to agree

146
00:16:07,026 --> 00:16:08,994
Poojaji...
- Who's that?

147
00:16:11,030 --> 00:16:12,998
Shiv. The one with the
high qualifications

148
00:16:14,033 --> 00:16:16,001
Who are you?
- l'm Shiv... Shiv Kapoor

149
00:16:17,036 --> 00:16:20,005
l see. And what are you doing here?
- l'm drowning my sorrows, Poojaji

150
00:16:22,041 --> 00:16:24,009
lt's my friend's second
wedding anniversary

151
00:16:25,044 --> 00:16:26,011
l had to come,
he dragged me here.

152
00:16:27,046 --> 00:16:29,014
Or l was only thinking about you.
- What? Who's this, Pooja?

153
00:16:31,050 --> 00:16:33,018
Shivji...
- Shivji?

154
00:16:35,054 --> 00:16:37,022
Right. Shiv Kapoor. And you folks?
- My brother and my sister-in-law

155
00:16:40,059 --> 00:16:41,026
Hasn't Papaji come?

156
00:16:43,062 --> 00:16:45,030
Papaji?
- Yes. Papa

157
00:16:47,066 --> 00:16:49,034
Have l said something wrong?
- Not at all

158
00:16:50,069 --> 00:16:52,037
Didn't l tell you, brother?
Papa=Boss; Boss=Papa...?

159
00:16:53,072 --> 00:16:54,039
That's just it

160
00:16:56,075 --> 00:16:57,042
Okay, l'll do it for you

161
00:16:58,077 --> 00:17:00,045
Very well then...
- l see. Very well then!

162
00:17:03,082 --> 00:17:05,050
How can you leave like this?
You're Pooja's friend

163
00:17:08,087 --> 00:17:10,089
You must eat with us tonight.
Pooja has ordered so much! Look

164
00:17:10,089 --> 00:17:12,057
So much of food...?
What are you celebrating?

165
00:17:15,094 --> 00:17:16,061
Celebrating the job, of course!
- Job?

166
00:17:21,100 --> 00:17:23,068
Jobs, of course! lsn't it
my duty to get employment...

167
00:17:25,104 --> 00:17:27,106
to every poor man, where l am?
- You'll give me a job, won't you?

168
00:17:27,106 --> 00:17:29,074
Yes, l will. Good bye...
- All right... good-bye

169
00:17:33,112 --> 00:17:34,079
Don't forget it, okay?
- What are you doing?

170
00:17:36,115 --> 00:17:38,083
Amazing! Your first day at work
and you're already employing others!

171
00:17:41,120 --> 00:17:43,088
l said my sister has a large heart!
This is how you must always be Pooja!

172
00:17:44,123 --> 00:17:46,091
He's a good boy, although he's poor.
You must certainly give him a job.

173
00:17:48,127 --> 00:17:49,094
Oh sure

174
00:17:51,130 --> 00:17:52,097
God! He's driving me up the wall!

175
00:17:55,134 --> 00:17:57,102
l'll have to do something about him!
The bloody hanger-on!

176
00:18:18,157 --> 00:18:20,125
Sir, l've finished my work for the day.
Even the work for tomorrow

177
00:18:23,162 --> 00:18:25,130
l've even sent that
detailed fax

178
00:18:31,170 --> 00:18:32,137
ls this all?

179
00:18:42,181 --> 00:18:44,149
l have something to discuss.
- Speak

180
00:18:46,185 --> 00:18:48,153
l have a friend, sir.
He's very highly qualified

181
00:18:50,189 --> 00:18:52,157
He stands first in sports.
And he has no vices at all

182
00:18:55,194 --> 00:18:57,162
Well? What am l to do?

183
00:18:59,198 --> 00:19:01,166
Sir, could you give him a job?

184
00:19:02,201 --> 00:19:04,169
All right. Send him here right now.
l'll employ him

185
00:19:14,213 --> 00:19:15,180
What job are you
going to give him, sir?

186
00:19:17,216 --> 00:19:19,184
l'll fire you and hire him instead.
- What?

187
00:19:20,219 --> 00:19:21,186
lt isn't even a week since
you've joined this office...

188
00:19:23,222 --> 00:19:25,190
and you're already finding
other people jobs

189
00:19:26,225 --> 00:19:28,193
Work sincerely, if you wish to.
Else, l'll have to show you the door

190
00:19:39,238 --> 00:19:41,206
l'm late! lt's 9:00 already!
- lt's 9:00 ! l'm late!

191
00:19:46,245 --> 00:19:48,213
Why don't the two of you wake up
early, if you don't want to be late?

192
00:19:49,248 --> 00:19:50,215
You are both just the same!

193
00:19:54,253 --> 00:19:55,220
Where's my key now?
- l'm getting very late, brother

194
00:19:56,255 --> 00:19:58,223
Please drop me at the office.
- Are you mad, Pooja?

195
00:19:59,258 --> 00:20:02,227
My office is in this direction,
yours is in that! No way! lmpossible!

196
00:20:04,263 --> 00:20:06,231
Greetings, sir.
- Bhiku Singh? What're you doing here?

197
00:20:07,266 --> 00:20:08,233
Running an errand for the boss, sir.
- For C.P. ? l see

198
00:20:10,269 --> 00:20:12,237
Who's this?
- lt's my boss's car.

199
00:20:13,272 --> 00:20:15,240
He's going in the same direction.
Ask him to give me a lift

200
00:20:17,276 --> 00:20:20,245
Can you drop my sister at
Connaught Place, Bhiku Singh?

201
00:20:21,280 --> 00:20:22,247
Go on. Hurry up

202
00:20:40,299 --> 00:20:42,267
Pooja...?

203
00:20:53,312 --> 00:20:55,280
Poojaji! Listen to me!
One moment, please!

204
00:20:56,315 --> 00:20:57,282
One moment!

205
00:21:04,323 --> 00:21:05,290
Listen to me!

206
00:21:09,328 --> 00:21:10,295
One minute!

207
00:21:12,331 --> 00:21:14,299
At least roll down the window!

208
00:21:15,334 --> 00:21:18,303
lt's Shiv Kapoor!
l met you at the office, remember?

209
00:21:31,350 --> 00:21:34,319
Thank you, Bhiku Singh.
You may go

210
00:21:36,355 --> 00:21:38,323
Where did he spring from?

211
00:21:39,358 --> 00:21:42,327
l've been calling out to you and
you wouldn't even look back at me

212
00:21:43,362 --> 00:21:44,329
l've been following your car
on my bike

213
00:21:45,364 --> 00:21:47,332
Really?
- Oh yes. And how would you listen?

214
00:21:49,368 --> 00:21:51,336
lt's such a big car.
Fully air-conditioned

215
00:21:52,371 --> 00:21:54,339
Your windows were shut.
How can you be blamed?

216
00:21:55,374 --> 00:21:57,342
Well? What is it?
- Have you seen today's newspaper?

217
00:21:59,378 --> 00:22:01,346
Have you?
- What does it say?

218
00:22:02,381 --> 00:22:04,383
Your office has advertised again!
How could they, when you're around?

219
00:22:04,383 --> 00:22:07,352
Your Papa will once again get a call
and l'll lose my job, won't l?

220
00:22:09,388 --> 00:22:11,356
You're so naive.
You just don't understand

221
00:22:14,393 --> 00:22:16,361
To remain in circulation! One has
to do it to fool people. See?

222
00:22:18,397 --> 00:22:19,364
l see

223
00:22:23,402 --> 00:22:25,370
But why must you worry?
l'm very much here

224
00:22:26,405 --> 00:22:28,373
l've spoken to Papa.
Your job is confirmed

225
00:22:29,408 --> 00:22:31,376
Confirmed? May l meet him then?
- Meet Papa?

226
00:22:32,411 --> 00:22:33,378
Yes. l have an interview with him.
- Really?

227
00:22:34,413 --> 00:22:36,381
Listen, be very careful
during the interview

228
00:22:37,416 --> 00:22:39,384
Nobody must know that
l have recommended you.

229
00:22:40,419 --> 00:22:41,386
Or you'll lose the job.
Not even my Papa, okay?

230
00:22:42,421 --> 00:22:44,389
Go on now.
- May l?

231
00:22:46,425 --> 00:22:48,393
Be very careful

232
00:23:14,453 --> 00:23:16,421
You? What are you doing here?

233
00:23:17,456 --> 00:23:19,424
How did you get here?
- l found you at last, didn't l?

234
00:23:20,459 --> 00:23:22,427
Laddoos, Poojaji.
- How did you know l was here?

235
00:23:24,463 --> 00:23:26,431
When will your friends help?
Those Anju's and Sush's...

236
00:23:27,466 --> 00:23:30,435
you have an amazing friends' circle!
They were only too happy to tell me

237
00:23:31,470 --> 00:23:33,438
Laddoos...?
- Come to the point. What is it?

238
00:23:34,473 --> 00:23:36,441
Okay, where is your hand...?
- Let go! What are you up to?

239
00:23:40,479 --> 00:23:42,447
Ever since you shook
hands with me...

240
00:23:44,483 --> 00:23:46,451
my life has changed for the better.
- What happened?

241
00:23:49,488 --> 00:23:50,455
Your Papa has taken your advise

242
00:23:52,491 --> 00:23:53,458
He has employed me as
the General Manager!

243
00:23:54,493 --> 00:23:55,460
What? What are you talking about?

244
00:23:58,497 --> 00:24:00,465
Why're you so surprised?
You're the one who did it

245
00:24:02,501 --> 00:24:04,469
Have some laddoos, Poojaji.
Made with clarified-butter

246
00:24:08,507 --> 00:24:09,474
l bought them from Bengali Market.
Have some

247
00:24:10,509 --> 00:24:11,476
That's enough.
- Enough? Have a whole laddoo

248
00:24:12,511 --> 00:24:14,479
No, l don't have a whole laddoo.
- No? And l swallow half a dozen!

249
00:24:16,515 --> 00:24:18,483
Give some to your brother and...
- No. Not them!

250
00:24:19,518 --> 00:24:21,486
Why not? Give them some, too.
- Don't disturb them!

251
00:24:22,521 --> 00:24:24,489
Give them some...
- l've heard you talking, Shivji

252
00:24:27,526 --> 00:24:29,494
This is just what l
expected from you, Pooja

253
00:24:30,529 --> 00:24:32,497
You've got this capable boy
a job at last

254
00:24:33,532 --> 00:24:34,499
See what a large heart my sister has?
And you...

255
00:24:35,534 --> 00:24:38,503
Not just large-hearted...
she's a magnanimous Delhi-ite!

256
00:24:40,539 --> 00:24:42,507
Know what? You do have
a beautiful sister!

257
00:24:43,542 --> 00:24:45,510
Shut up, feller! And put
those laddoos away!

258
00:24:46,545 --> 00:24:48,513
Let me watch Aishwarya Rai!
- Don't be angry, Sardarji

259
00:24:49,548 --> 00:24:51,516
l've got a job today.
Have some laddoos.

260
00:24:52,551 --> 00:24:54,519
Congrats! l'll have two laddoos.
- One for me...!

261
00:25:09,568 --> 00:25:10,535
Congratulations, General Manager!

262
00:25:11,570 --> 00:25:15,529
This Hyderabadi will now treat you
to the most delectable food!

263
00:25:19,578 --> 00:25:21,546
Thanks a lot, my friend

264
00:25:22,581 --> 00:25:24,549
lt's only after l met you that
l embarked on this lovely journey

265
00:25:25,584 --> 00:25:29,543
Had you hung around the other day,
you wouldn't have got this post

266
00:25:30,589 --> 00:25:32,557
You'd have been hanging,
lower down in the ladder

267
00:25:33,592 --> 00:25:34,559
True. lt's all thanks to Poojaji

268
00:25:36,595 --> 00:25:37,562
As long as l live,
l'll worship only Pooja

269
00:25:39,598 --> 00:25:40,565
Pooja? Pooja who?
The manager?

270
00:25:43,602 --> 00:25:46,571
Come on! You're giving the employer
the status of an employee?

271
00:25:48,607 --> 00:25:51,576
This is the limit! Thanks to her,
so many poor guys have found jobs

272
00:25:53,612 --> 00:25:56,581
Take my case. Hadn't she put in a word
for me to her father, the employer...

273
00:25:57,616 --> 00:25:59,618
could we have been chatting in
this posh, air-conditioned office?

274
00:25:59,618 --> 00:26:00,585
What a shame! You're making
my head swim with rubbish

275
00:26:06,625 --> 00:26:08,593
That girl has made
a sucker out of you

276
00:26:09,628 --> 00:26:11,596
She got rid of you the other day
and snatched your job. That's it!

277
00:26:14,633 --> 00:26:16,601
What does that mean?
- l mean, she's just...

278
00:26:18,637 --> 00:26:19,604
an executive manager. Nothing else!

279
00:26:25,644 --> 00:26:29,603
Which means, the boss
isn't dear papa at all?

280
00:26:31,650 --> 00:26:33,618
Chopra, the old fossil,
is a rotten old fig!

281
00:26:35,654 --> 00:26:36,621
And he's still a bachelor!

282
00:26:38,657 --> 00:26:40,625
You mean Pooja didn't
recommend me at all?

283
00:26:41,660 --> 00:26:42,627
My dear naive boy!

284
00:26:46,665 --> 00:26:49,634
Recommend you? She's been
cutting you out all the way!

285
00:26:51,670 --> 00:26:52,637
Really? So she took me for a ride!
- Yes.

286
00:26:56,675 --> 00:26:57,642
And took me all over Delhi!
- Oh yes!

287
00:26:58,677 --> 00:26:59,644
She has turned out to be
quite an actress!

288
00:27:00,679 --> 00:27:02,647
Dil-phenk, call her immediately.
l'll fix her

289
00:27:05,684 --> 00:27:07,652
l'll call her. And you
must teach her a lesson

290
00:27:09,688 --> 00:27:10,655
lt's your right.
You're the General Manager!

291
00:27:11,690 --> 00:27:12,657
Let her come. l'll show her

292
00:27:13,692 --> 00:27:16,661
l'll teach her such a lesson, she'll
never think of conning anyone again

293
00:27:24,703 --> 00:27:25,670
Do come

294
00:27:26,705 --> 00:27:27,672
My word!

295
00:27:32,711 --> 00:27:34,679
Sit down. Why're you standing?
- How can l sit in your presence?

296
00:27:39,718 --> 00:27:40,685
You have done so much for me

297
00:27:42,721 --> 00:27:44,689
You took my destiny into your hands
and made my life

298
00:27:46,725 --> 00:27:48,693
You've recommended me to your Papa
at the breakfast table!

299
00:27:51,730 --> 00:27:53,698
l do that very often.
- ln a flying Mercedes car...

300
00:27:55,734 --> 00:27:58,703
you weren't thinking about yourself.
You thought of me

301
00:28:03,742 --> 00:28:06,711
lnstead of the Executive Manager,
you made me the General Manager!

302
00:28:11,750 --> 00:28:13,718
You're such a great person.
lt's amazing, Poojaji!

303
00:28:16,755 --> 00:28:18,723
Would you like to have some tea?
- Tea...?

304
00:28:27,766 --> 00:28:28,733
What...?

305
00:28:30,769 --> 00:28:31,736
You dare make a fool out of me?

306
00:28:34,773 --> 00:28:35,740
Shiv? Call me ''Sir'' !

307
00:28:39,778 --> 00:28:42,747
Poojaji! l went about worshipping you.
And you kept making a fool out of me!

308
00:28:47,786 --> 00:28:49,754
The pampered daughter of the
dear Papa...

309
00:28:50,789 --> 00:28:53,758
you're a sympathiser of the poor
and recommend them, don't you?

310
00:28:54,793 --> 00:28:56,761
You played around with me! You conned
me the first time we met...

311
00:28:58,797 --> 00:29:00,765
and walked away with my job!
And as if that wasn't enough...

312
00:29:01,800 --> 00:29:04,769
you polished off fancy delicacies with
your brother at the 5-star hotel!

313
00:29:10,809 --> 00:29:12,777
Like a madman, l went around Delhi
looking for you...

314
00:29:15,814 --> 00:29:17,782
and you were sitting in the theater,
watching the latest movie!

315
00:29:19,818 --> 00:29:21,786
And l still got laddoos made
for a stone-hearted girl like you!

316
00:29:22,821 --> 00:29:24,789
With clarified-butter!
So tell me now, Poojaji...

317
00:29:28,827 --> 00:29:31,796
what am l to do with you?
Must l kill you? Or let you go?

318
00:29:32,831 --> 00:29:33,798
Tell me

319
00:29:35,834 --> 00:29:38,803
l agree to any punishment you
hand out to me, Mr General Manager

320
00:29:44,843 --> 00:29:46,811
Will you do as l say?
- Yes, l will

321
00:29:49,848 --> 00:29:51,816
Will you marry me?
- Yes, l will

322
00:30:16,875 --> 00:30:18,843
''The way you look,
tells me...''

323
00:30:25,884 --> 00:30:26,851
''l'm the one you love''

324
00:30:32,891 --> 00:30:34,859
''The way you talk,
tells me...''

325
00:30:40,899 --> 00:30:42,867
''l'm the one you could die for''

326
00:30:49,908 --> 00:30:51,876
''l'd teach you the way of loving...''

327
00:30:53,912 --> 00:30:55,880
''and lay down my life for you,
my love''

328
00:30:57,916 --> 00:30:59,884
''You set my heart racing,
you taught me lessons in love...''

329
00:31:02,921 --> 00:31:04,889
''you have accepted me,
you're my crazy lover''

330
00:31:06,925 --> 00:31:08,893
''We have taken a vow...
we will never part''

331
00:32:11,990 --> 00:32:13,958
''This is a new story,
this is a new friendship''

332
00:32:18,997 --> 00:32:20,965
''This is my first love...
you're my first beloved''

333
00:32:27,005 --> 00:32:28,973
''Under the blue skies,
two young hearts meet in love''

334
00:32:38,016 --> 00:32:39,984
''The way you breathe,
it tells me...''

335
00:32:46,024 --> 00:32:46,991
''l'm the one you love''

336
00:32:55,033 --> 00:32:57,001
''The way you lurch forth,
it tells me...''

337
00:33:04,042 --> 00:33:06,010
''l'm the one you could die for''

338
00:33:32,070 --> 00:33:34,038
''l'm not in my senses;
you realise nothing''

339
00:33:39,077 --> 00:33:41,045
''lt's the effect my love
has had on you''

340
00:33:47,085 --> 00:33:49,053
''Let's lose ourselves
in each other...''

341
00:33:53,091 --> 00:33:55,059
''so that no one in the world
can ever see us''

342
00:33:57,095 --> 00:33:59,063
''Every secret of your dreams
tells me...''

343
00:34:08,106 --> 00:34:09,073
''l'm the one you love''

344
00:34:16,114 --> 00:34:18,082
''The way you embrace me, tells
me..''

345
00:34:23,121 --> 00:34:25,089
''l'm the one you
could die for''

346
00:34:30,128 --> 00:34:31,095
''l'd teach you the way to love...''

347
00:34:36,134 --> 00:34:38,102
''and lay down my life
for you, my love''

348
00:34:40,138 --> 00:34:42,106
''You set my heart beating,
you taught me lessons in love...''

349
00:34:43,141 --> 00:34:45,109
''you have accepted me,
you're my crazy lover''

350
00:34:49,147 --> 00:34:51,115
''We have sworn, we have vowed...
never to part''

351
00:36:08,226 --> 00:36:10,194
lt's morning already.
But your mischief isn't over

352
00:36:12,230 --> 00:36:14,198
Don't ruin the General Manager's
mood, okay?

353
00:36:20,238 --> 00:36:22,206
l'm the only General Manager
in this house!

354
00:36:24,242 --> 00:36:26,210
l didn't deny that. You're the
General Manager of my heart too.

355
00:36:30,248 --> 00:36:31,215
lt's amazing! l sometimes wonder...

356
00:36:34,252 --> 00:36:35,219
how l could to sleep alone
all these years.

357
00:36:37,255 --> 00:36:39,223
What must the poor bachelors
be going through?

358
00:36:41,259 --> 00:36:43,227
Are wives meant only for this?
You men are all alike!

359
00:36:45,263 --> 00:36:47,231
You just won't improve.
- lf we improve, madam...

360
00:36:48,266 --> 00:36:50,234
what happens of you women?
- lt's pointless arguing with you

361
00:36:52,270 --> 00:36:54,238
Get up now, bathe
and leave for work

362
00:36:55,273 --> 00:36:56,240
Or we won't even have this house
the company has given us

363
00:36:57,275 --> 00:36:58,242
Get up...
- No

364
00:37:00,278 --> 00:37:01,245
Must l go to the office today?
- l've given up the job

365
00:37:04,282 --> 00:37:07,285
lf you don't go to work,
what will we live on?

366
00:37:07,285 --> 00:37:10,254
Simple. We'll live on love and air.
l'll eat you up too!

367
00:37:11,289 --> 00:37:13,257
This is my right!
- No rights. Just get up

368
00:37:15,293 --> 00:37:16,260
See who's at the door...
go on!

369
00:37:18,296 --> 00:37:19,263
Get up, please!

370
00:37:25,303 --> 00:37:26,270
You're very lazy! Get up and go.
@ 02/05/11902

371
00:37:34,312 --> 00:37:35,279
Who are you?

372
00:37:48,326 --> 00:37:50,294
Milk!
- What?

373
00:37:51,329 --> 00:37:53,297
l'm the milkmaid, sir.
My name is Kismis

374
00:37:58,336 --> 00:37:59,303
Take it

375
00:38:04,342 --> 00:38:05,309
How much?

376
00:38:07,345 --> 00:38:10,314
Accounts are settled at
the end of the month, sir

377
00:38:13,351 --> 00:38:16,320
You're a newcomer?
- Yes. We're newcomers

378
00:38:17,355 --> 00:38:20,324
So tell me... is one packet enough?
Or must l give more?

379
00:38:24,362 --> 00:38:25,329
One should be enough. Why?

380
00:38:28,366 --> 00:38:31,335
l ask, because people in this
building use lots of milk

381
00:38:34,372 --> 00:38:37,341
One is enough.
- l'll leave then, sir

382
00:38:46,384 --> 00:38:48,352
l say, sir...
- What?

383
00:38:50,388 --> 00:38:52,356
Lend me a hand.
- What?

384
00:38:54,392 --> 00:38:57,361
With this burden.
- Sure. One moment

385
00:39:02,400 --> 00:39:04,368
God! l've been had!

386
00:39:07,405 --> 00:39:09,373
May l say something, sir?
- Go ahead

387
00:39:10,408 --> 00:39:13,377
You're a very decent man.
A very nice gentleman

388
00:39:15,413 --> 00:39:18,382
You have a handsome face...
you worthy of befriending, sir

389
00:39:21,419 --> 00:39:23,387
Really?
- Oh yes. May l leave, friend?

390
00:39:28,426 --> 00:39:29,393
Tomorrow morning then

391
00:39:40,438 --> 00:39:42,406
Has the friend left?

392
00:39:45,443 --> 00:39:48,412
Yes, she has.
lt was the milkmaid

393
00:39:49,447 --> 00:39:52,416
So it's going to take so much of
time to fetch milk every morning?

394
00:39:54,452 --> 00:39:56,420
You could've seen her off downstairs.
- l was only helping her...

395
00:39:57,455 --> 00:40:00,424
and what are you thinking about?
A milkmaid and l...? C'mon Pooja!

396
00:40:01,459 --> 00:40:05,418
l know you men very well.
Give me the milk

397
00:40:08,466 --> 00:40:10,434
First give me what is mine

398
00:40:12,470 --> 00:40:13,437
What?

399
00:40:15,473 --> 00:40:18,442
This lungi and kurta you're
wearing, are mine

400
00:40:19,477 --> 00:40:22,446
Go on. Take it off.
- Come inside. l'll give it to you

401
00:40:25,483 --> 00:40:26,450
Now. Right now

402
00:40:30,488 --> 00:40:33,457
Have you gone mad...?
People are watching!

403
00:40:37,495 --> 00:40:38,462
Let me go!

404
00:40:50,508 --> 00:40:53,477
Shiv, l'm going to take the
milk from tomorrow. Not you

405
00:41:05,523 --> 00:41:08,492
This is funny. He calls us here
and doesn't turn up himself

406
00:41:09,527 --> 00:41:11,495
l can't understand why he said,
we mustn't tell Pooja

407
00:41:15,533 --> 00:41:17,501
They haven't had a fight, have they?
Your sister always itches for a fight

408
00:41:18,536 --> 00:41:20,504
Not more than you do.
- Taking up for your sister again?

409
00:41:21,539 --> 00:41:24,508
She's lucky to have found a
husband like him in such times

410
00:41:25,543 --> 00:41:26,510
Here he is

411
00:41:27,545 --> 00:41:28,512
Sorry, folks

412
00:41:30,548 --> 00:41:31,515
Can't help this Delhi traffic.
l'd have zoomed in on a bike

413
00:41:32,550 --> 00:41:34,518
Ever since l got this car,
l get stuck everywhere

414
00:41:35,553 --> 00:41:38,522
What is the secret that you call us
here without even telling Pooja?

415
00:41:39,557 --> 00:41:41,525
What's the day today?
- 15th of December

416
00:41:42,560 --> 00:41:44,528
And tomorrow?
- The 16th of December. So what?

417
00:41:45,563 --> 00:41:47,531
What, eh? You forget it, after
all the years she spent with you?

418
00:41:48,566 --> 00:41:50,534
And l remember everything in
just a few months with her

419
00:41:51,569 --> 00:41:53,537
Tomorrow's Pooja birthday.
- l know. So listen...

420
00:41:54,572 --> 00:41:57,541
We'll first buy a huge cake.
We'll pack some food...

421
00:42:01,579 --> 00:42:05,538
buy lots of balloons and gifts
and surprise her at midnight!

422
00:42:08,586 --> 00:42:11,555
And l thought my husband had
brought me out to the amusement park

423
00:42:12,590 --> 00:42:15,559
l'm not leaving without
sitting on the giant-wheel

424
00:42:18,596 --> 00:42:19,563
As if it's your age
to sit on the giant-wheel

425
00:42:20,598 --> 00:42:22,566
What...?
- No age-bar to enjoy life

426
00:42:24,602 --> 00:42:25,569
We'll do just as your wife says

427
00:42:28,606 --> 00:42:31,575
Come on, brother.
- lt's very high! l'm not sitting in it

428
00:42:34,612 --> 00:42:36,580
Come on...
- No! l'm scared, Shiv!

429
00:42:37,615 --> 00:42:39,583
Go with her instead.
- No. The couple sit together

430
00:42:41,619 --> 00:42:43,587
Come on...
- Are you coming too?

431
00:42:44,622 --> 00:42:45,589
lf l don't come back alive,
look after my bitch

432
00:42:46,624 --> 00:42:49,593
What rubbish! Come!
- Look after my Kittu!

433
00:42:54,632 --> 00:42:57,601
Not too high, mister.
l'm scared

434
00:44:32,730 --> 00:44:34,698
What happened? Why's it jammed?
- Don't worry

435
00:44:37,735 --> 00:44:40,704
lt'll start up again. Enjoy the sight
of Delhi from this height, my love!

436
00:44:50,748 --> 00:44:51,715
Let's spend the night chatting

437
00:44:59,757 --> 00:45:01,725
Will you be my friend?

438
00:45:03,761 --> 00:45:06,730
My name is Shiv Kapoor.
l have a wife. A missus

439
00:45:10,768 --> 00:45:12,736
Her name is Pooja

440
00:45:17,775 --> 00:45:19,743
Pooja, my darling wife

441
00:45:25,783 --> 00:45:27,751
l say, brother-in-law...
- Yes?

442
00:45:31,789 --> 00:45:33,757
lt's already midnight, l say

443
00:45:35,793 --> 00:45:36,760
Oh yes. All the way

444
00:45:42,800 --> 00:45:44,768
Today's your wife's birthday?

445
00:45:51,809 --> 00:45:54,778
But it's so sad.
You're stuck here... with me

446
00:46:05,823 --> 00:46:07,791
Looks like they're fixing it

447
00:46:08,826 --> 00:46:11,795
l wonder how many more jolts
l'm going to get tonight

448
00:46:14,832 --> 00:46:17,801
Oh yes. l don't know how many jolts
this husband will take tonight!

449
00:46:59,877 --> 00:47:01,845
Where were you?

450
00:47:05,883 --> 00:47:07,851
First tell me where you were.
- l'll tell you. l'll explain

451
00:47:08,886 --> 00:47:11,855
l know you will believe what l say.
- Now tell me the truth...

452
00:47:13,891 --> 00:47:16,860
only the truth. Speak up!
- l was in the office all night

453
00:47:19,897 --> 00:47:22,866
There was something only l could do.
l knew it was your birthday...

454
00:47:23,901 --> 00:47:25,869
but l couldn't disobey the boss.
- Really?

455
00:47:27,905 --> 00:47:30,874
But l kept calling the office
all night. Nobody took the call

456
00:47:33,911 --> 00:47:36,880
All the lines were disconnected.
They were held up

457
00:47:37,915 --> 00:47:40,884
lt was as if l was in the skies
and you were here, on earth

458
00:47:43,921 --> 00:47:45,889
Who baked it?
- l did

459
00:47:46,924 --> 00:47:48,892
Shall we cut it?
- No

460
00:47:49,927 --> 00:47:52,896
Do you think l'll give in so easily?
lt's a nice story...

