The secretary has left us
in a mess of schedules...

783
01:31:24,564 --> 01:31:25,531
what have you thought about that?

784
01:31:26,566 --> 01:31:28,534
This is the problems we have when
secretaries turn producers

785
01:31:30,570 --> 01:31:31,537
Where will we find
someone honest now?

786
01:31:32,572 --> 01:31:34,540
We mustn't a crooked man!
Our hero-ji's such a simple man...

787
01:31:40,580 --> 01:31:42,548
they'd rip him apart.
- So where will l find the man?

788
01:31:45,585 --> 01:31:47,553
lt could be a woman too, right?
- A woman?

789
01:31:49,589 --> 01:31:51,557
Can a woman handle my affairs?

790
01:31:54,594 --> 01:31:56,562
When l can look after your house,
your clothes, your food, everything...

791
01:32:01,601 --> 01:32:03,569
why can't a girl look after your dates,
your schedules and your accounts?

792
01:32:09,609 --> 01:32:11,577
lf we could find an honest
and trustworthy girl...

793
01:32:14,614 --> 01:32:16,582
but where will l find one?
- We've found her already

794
01:32:20,620 --> 01:32:21,587
You've found her already?
- Yes

795
01:32:22,622 --> 01:32:23,589
And who is she?

796
01:32:27,627 --> 01:32:28,594
Where is she?
- Just a minute

797
01:32:44,644 --> 01:32:45,611
Hero-ji, this is Pooja

798
01:32:48,648 --> 01:32:50,616
Neha, the designer's assistant,
has sent her over

799
01:32:55,655 --> 01:32:57,623
Why talk in French?
l'd rather you did it in Tamil

800
01:33:01,661 --> 01:33:02,628
She's a very good girl

801
01:33:04,664 --> 01:33:06,632
You must interview her, okay?

802
01:33:18,678 --> 01:33:20,646
So, you're...?
- Let me tell you at the outset, sir

803
01:33:25,685 --> 01:33:27,653
l know nothing about
the film business

804
01:33:30,690 --> 01:33:31,657
So how will you handle this job?

805
01:33:39,699 --> 01:33:41,667
Neha and your staff asked me
to meet you. So, l...

806
01:33:47,707 --> 01:33:49,675
l see. So what are you
well-versed with?

807
01:33:57,717 --> 01:33:58,684
l'm familiar with computers

808
01:33:59,719 --> 01:34:01,687
l know a lot about programming
and accounting. That's all

809
01:34:04,724 --> 01:34:07,693
That's all? And that is enough

810
01:34:09,729 --> 01:34:11,697
The knowledge you have
is enough for this job

811
01:34:13,733 --> 01:34:15,701
You could say you've landed the job
- Pardon me?

812
01:34:17,737 --> 01:34:19,705
Yes. lf my staff says you're good,
you really are good

813
01:34:25,745 --> 01:34:27,713
So tell me how do we
sweeten your tongue now?

814
01:34:28,748 --> 01:34:29,715
With these sweetmeats!

815
01:34:32,752 --> 01:34:33,719
Here you are. Offer Pooja the sweets!

816
01:34:34,754 --> 01:34:36,722
Wow! Here you are. Have some sweets.
- Go on

817
01:34:46,766 --> 01:34:47,733
No small pieces. Take a whole laddoo

818
01:34:48,768 --> 01:34:50,736
Fortunate are those who get
to eat all these goodies

819
01:34:53,773 --> 01:34:54,740
No taunts, hero-ji

820
01:34:56,776 --> 01:34:58,744
But you may have two laddoos
to celebrate her arrival

821
01:35:00,780 --> 01:35:02,748
Not two... eat up all there is!
- Thanks. Keep this in the car

822
01:35:07,787 --> 01:35:08,754
You can report to duty tomorrow

823
01:35:15,795 --> 01:35:17,763
Hero-ji has appointed a new secretary.
She'll be here any moment

824
01:35:21,801 --> 01:35:23,769
Pooja is here! All the mess
will now be cleared!

825
01:35:29,809 --> 01:35:31,777
Come here. This is Pooja.
The new secretary

826
01:35:33,813 --> 01:35:35,781
Whatever you've got to ask,
you will now ask her. Okay?

827
01:35:41,821 --> 01:35:42,788
Namaste

828
01:35:47,827 --> 01:35:48,794
What are you doing, Babban Miyan?

829
01:35:50,830 --> 01:35:51,797
lt's a 2 'o clock shift. And you
wake me up early in the morning!

830
01:35:52,832 --> 01:35:53,799
l know. Apart from film shootings...

831
01:35:54,834 --> 01:35:55,801
there are many things you've
got to do on your own

832
01:35:56,836 --> 01:35:58,804
This big house and all those people
downstairs... who'll handle them?

833
01:36:02,842 --> 01:36:04,810
You have no one of your own either.
- So what are you folks worth?

834
01:36:11,851 --> 01:36:13,819
Okay, but there are things
we can't do. Only you can

835
01:36:15,855 --> 01:36:17,823
And this is something
only you can do, hero-ji. Not we

836
01:36:23,863 --> 01:36:25,831
Such as...?
- Such as, signing documents

837
01:36:28,868 --> 01:36:30,836
lssuing cheques. Who'll do all that?
- You do it, Miyan

838
01:36:31,871 --> 01:36:33,839
No thank you. By God, don't
trust people in the world so much

839
01:36:36,876 --> 01:36:38,844
lt's a terrible world!
Money's everything for them

840
01:36:40,880 --> 01:36:42,848
May l say my lines now?
- Sure, go ahead

841
01:36:44,884 --> 01:36:46,852
May l go for a bath?
- Sure.

842
01:36:47,887 --> 01:36:48,854
But come back soon. And see...

843
01:36:51,891 --> 01:36:52,858
how the world is waiting for you

844
01:37:01,901 --> 01:37:03,869
You said there were a lot of people.
There's not a soul here

845
01:37:11,911 --> 01:37:12,878
The producers must have fled

846
01:37:18,918 --> 01:37:19,885
My mistake

847
01:37:23,923 --> 01:37:24,890
Will you stop flying please?

848
01:37:25,925 --> 01:37:27,893
He said there were producers here
to meet me. Where have they gone?

849
01:37:28,928 --> 01:37:30,896
Bingo! The wonder girl
has worked a miracle!

850
01:37:33,933 --> 01:37:35,901
She brewed such a broth
that everything fell in place!

851
01:37:39,939 --> 01:37:40,906
lf you guys are going to say
everything, what lines will l say?

852
01:37:41,941 --> 01:37:43,909
Now tell me what happened.
- Pooja-ji! The wonder girl!

853
01:37:49,949 --> 01:37:51,917
The way she handled the producers,
l could only watch in amazement!

854
01:37:54,954 --> 01:37:56,922
l swear it on God, my eyes can
never make a mistake!

855
01:38:01,961 --> 01:38:03,929
This is the right girl, hero-ji.
- Really? And where is Pooja-ji?

856
01:38:12,972 --> 01:38:13,939
Meaning...?
- She's working. On the computer

857
01:38:20,980 --> 01:38:22,948
Are you through?
- l'm doing it... l'm still at it

858
01:38:43,002 --> 01:38:44,970
Sir, l've sorted out those dates
that were messed up

859
01:38:49,008 --> 01:38:50,976
Accounts of money we've
received against shooting,...

860
01:38:52,011 --> 01:38:52,978
l've fed in the computer

861
01:38:55,014 --> 01:38:56,982
l've fixed your appointments with
directors, during lunch-break...

862
01:39:00,019 --> 01:39:01,987
so you won't be disturbed.
You've got to read some agreements...

863
01:39:04,023 --> 01:39:06,992
and sign them now.
- Okay

864
01:39:09,028 --> 01:39:09,995
ls all the work over?
- Yes

865
01:39:13,032 --> 01:39:13,999
Nothing remaining?
- No

866
01:39:20,039 --> 01:39:22,007
ln which case, why must you come here
all thirty days in a month?

867
01:39:25,044 --> 01:39:27,012
Come just for a day.
- One day?

868
01:39:30,049 --> 01:39:32,017
Yes. What's the date today?
The first

869
01:39:33,052 --> 01:39:34,019
So we'll meet up again
on the first of the next month

870
01:39:35,054 --> 01:39:36,021
lt's pack up for you.
You may go

871
01:39:40,059 --> 01:39:42,027
What are you saying, hero-ji?
You've ruined all our joy!

872
01:39:44,063 --> 01:39:46,031
Pooja-ji handled everything so
quickly with her intelligence...

873
01:39:48,067 --> 01:39:50,035
and you just won't praise her!
- You've messed up the grease-paint!

874
01:39:56,075 --> 01:39:58,043
She completed a month's work
in just one day

875
01:40:01,080 --> 01:40:02,047
So what will she do for the
rest of the 29 days? What?

876
01:40:03,082 --> 01:40:05,050
You've worked for a day, Pooja.
You get paid for a day's work too

877
01:40:09,088 --> 01:40:11,056
Goodness isn't appreciated!
The same amount of work...

878
01:40:12,091 --> 01:40:13,058
the previous secretary took
2 months to complete!

879
01:40:14,093 --> 01:40:16,061
And you paid him double the salary!
- No wonder he became a producer!

880
01:40:20,099 --> 01:40:22,067
And you won't appreciate Pooja for
completing everything so soon!

881
01:40:24,103 --> 01:40:25,070
Where will l break my head now...?

882
01:40:44,123 --> 01:40:45,090
He's laughing!

883
01:40:47,126 --> 01:40:49,094
Sir, you're laughing?
- l was only joking

884
01:40:56,135 --> 01:40:57,102
And you talk of breaking heads?

885
01:41:09,148 --> 01:41:11,116
Where were you all these days?
Where?

886
01:41:14,153 --> 01:41:16,121
l must say, you folks do
have an eye for people

887
01:41:18,157 --> 01:41:20,125
Now tell me, how many years contract
do l draw up for her?

888
01:41:22,161 --> 01:41:24,129
20 years? 25 years...?
- For a lifetime. Forever, sir!

889
01:41:28,167 --> 01:41:30,135
No secretary works like this.
Only a wife does...

890
01:41:32,171 --> 01:41:33,138
the one made for you, does!

891
01:41:49,188 --> 01:41:51,156
Have l said something wrong?
- You always say the wrong line

892
01:41:52,191 --> 01:41:54,159
What did l say?
- l'll tell you later

893
01:42:03,202 --> 01:42:05,170
You mustn't take offense
at what they say

894
01:42:06,205 --> 01:42:08,173
Because l'm so lonely, they're
always cooking things up for me

895
01:42:12,211 --> 01:42:13,178
They aren't bad at heart

896
01:42:14,213 --> 01:42:15,180
You have handled everything
in just a day, l'm impressed

897
01:42:16,215 --> 01:42:18,183
Know what? l had this problem
for quite a few days

898
01:42:24,223 --> 01:42:26,191
l couldn't decide what was right
and what was wrong

899
01:42:27,226 --> 01:42:28,193
But now l think everything
will be all right

900
01:42:29,228 --> 01:42:31,196
Get on with your work.
Please carry on

901
01:42:44,243 --> 01:42:46,211
Poojaji, please don't feel bad
about anything

902
01:42:48,247 --> 01:42:50,215
Now that you're here,
it's going to be fun

903
01:42:52,251 --> 01:42:54,219
We'll do good work and
spend our days in fun

904
01:42:56,255 --> 01:42:58,223
We won't even know when
the climes change

905
01:44:38,357 --> 01:44:39,324
Raj, give me just two minutes. Please

906
01:44:41,360 --> 01:44:42,327
Chinni, please come here

907
01:44:46,365 --> 01:44:47,332
What is it, Pooja?

908
01:44:49,368 --> 01:44:50,335
There was a call from
Mr Morani and Mr Soorma

909
01:44:51,370 --> 01:44:53,338
l think they want to discuss
dates personally with you

910
01:44:54,373 --> 01:44:56,341
So l'll meet up with them.
Just tell me when

911
01:44:57,376 --> 01:44:59,344
Anytime you wish.
l'll tell you your programme

912
01:45:02,381 --> 01:45:03,348
Raj, please let's have
another rehearsal

913
01:45:04,383 --> 01:45:06,351
lf l mess up this time, l'm
going to get a lot of scolding

914
01:45:07,386 --> 01:45:08,353
All right. Wait here, Pooja

915
01:45:11,390 --> 01:45:12,357
l'll speak my lines, okay?
- No, let's begin with my lines

916
01:45:13,392 --> 01:45:14,359
All right. Go ahead

917
01:45:15,394 --> 01:47:16,476
l'm so happy today...

918
01:47:19,518 --> 01:47:20,485
Where is she, Raja?
- Who?

919
01:47:23,522 --> 01:47:24,489
She

920
01:47:27,526 --> 01:47:28,493
Why need that when you
have this one?

921
01:47:30,529 --> 01:47:31,496
What?
- What does that mean?

922
01:47:35,534 --> 01:47:36,501
l'll tell you what it means

923
01:47:38,537 --> 01:47:40,505
Rascals! Have you nothing
better to do?

924
01:47:42,541 --> 01:47:44,509
Do you come here
only to bother girls?

925
01:47:45,544 --> 01:47:47,512
Have you been taught nothing better?
Can you only talk nonsense?

926
01:47:48,547 --> 01:47:49,514
Come here...

927
01:47:52,551 --> 01:47:53,518
l'm going to smash your face

928
01:47:55,554 --> 01:47:56,521
You won't be able to
face anyone again

929
01:47:57,556 --> 01:47:59,524
Your tongues wag a lot!
You want to have fun!

930
01:48:00,559 --> 01:48:02,527
You want girls, eh?
You want girls?

931
01:48:12,571 --> 01:48:13,538
Was this enough or do you
want some more fun?

932
01:48:14,573 --> 01:48:15,540
No! Enough!

933
01:48:16,575 --> 01:48:17,542
So when are you leaving the hotel?

934
01:48:18,577 --> 01:48:19,544
Today! Right now!
- Good

935
01:48:20,579 --> 01:48:22,547
Get lost soon.
- Sure we will

936
01:48:28,587 --> 01:48:30,555
Room No 420.
A room for frauds indeed.

937
01:48:32,591 --> 01:48:34,559
You must apologise to all
those you have insulted

938
01:48:36,595 --> 01:48:37,562
l'll wait for you

939
01:48:46,605 --> 01:48:47,572
Heroji, they're escaping

940
01:48:55,614 --> 01:48:57,582
Where are you guys going...?
Wait... you don't have to leave

941
01:48:58,617 --> 01:48:59,584
Leave after you watch the shooting.
- No thanks

942
01:49:01,620 --> 01:49:02,587
You must have fun!
- No thanks

943
01:49:03,622 --> 01:49:05,590
How can l let you leave like this?
Go after you see the shooting

944
01:49:06,625 --> 01:49:08,593
Come, l'll introduce you
to the whole unit

945
01:49:09,628 --> 01:49:11,596
This is the director.
Say namaste to him

946
01:49:13,632 --> 01:49:14,599
Namaste

947
01:49:15,634 --> 01:49:17,602
This is our heroine.
Pay your respects to her

948
01:49:18,637 --> 01:49:20,605
Our respects.
- This is my make-up man, Chinni

949
01:49:23,642 --> 01:49:24,609
Hello.
- Hello

950
01:49:25,644 --> 01:49:26,611
No hello. Touch his feet

951
01:49:29,648 --> 01:49:31,616
Go on. Take his blessings.
You've got to play the baddies

952
01:49:36,655 --> 01:49:38,623
You haven't met her. She's...
- Namaste, Pooja

953
01:49:43,662 --> 01:49:45,630
Namaste, Poojaji.
- Poojaji?

954
01:49:46,665 --> 01:49:48,633
Sister Pooja!
- Good. But try something new

955
01:49:50,669 --> 01:49:52,637
Something spontaneous.
- Praise the Lord, Sister Pooja

956
01:49:53,672 --> 01:49:55,640
Praise the Lord! You do have
respect for womenfolk

957
01:49:59,678 --> 01:50:00,645
You must come to the shoot tomorrow.
Oh yes, you must!

958
01:50:01,680 --> 01:50:03,648
Where are we shooting
tomorrow, Poojaji?

959
01:50:04,683 --> 01:50:05,650
We're shooting at the graveyard

960
01:50:06,685 --> 01:50:08,653
We're going to bury the dead.
You must attend!

961
01:50:10,689 --> 01:50:11,656
You must! Please!

962
01:50:14,693 --> 01:50:15,660
Don't make me lose my temper...
l might push you

963
01:50:18,697 --> 01:50:19,664
They've had it

964
01:50:26,705 --> 01:50:27,672
l'm sorry

965
01:50:30,709 --> 01:50:32,677
Stop giggling and attend
to my hair, Chinni

966
01:50:47,726 --> 01:50:48,693
What are you writing?

967
01:50:50,729 --> 01:50:51,696
What are you writing?
- Nothing

968
01:50:53,732 --> 01:50:54,699
Let me see what you're writing

969
01:51:07,746 --> 01:51:09,714
l knew you'd do something like this.
That you would resign

970
01:51:12,751 --> 01:51:14,719
This is how you girls are.
You flare up at everything

971
01:51:16,755 --> 01:51:17,722
Tell you what? Go into the
kitchen and smash things

972
01:51:18,757 --> 01:51:20,725
Your temper will cool down.
- You cooled down. By beating them up

973
01:51:28,767 --> 01:51:30,735
There wasn't a better way
of handling it, was there?

974
01:51:31,770 --> 01:51:33,738
Was it necessary to do all that?
- lt's like this, Pooja

975
01:51:36,775 --> 01:51:37,742
lt makes no difference to me
what they write or say about me

976
01:51:41,780 --> 01:51:42,747
Because my life is an open book

977
01:51:43,782 --> 01:51:45,750
But l know, it makes
a difference to you

978
01:51:47,786 --> 01:51:49,754
You can't tolerate it, because
you're not used to it

979
01:51:52,791 --> 01:51:54,759
So l did what l had to.
And you're angry with me?

980
01:51:56,795 --> 01:51:58,763
You're handing in your resignation?
- Please don't misunderstand me

981
01:52:00,799 --> 01:52:02,767
l don't want such a thing
to happen ever again

982
01:52:04,803 --> 01:52:06,771
They... they could say
anything about you and me

983
01:52:08,807 --> 01:52:10,775
So let them!
l'm not backing out, am l?

984
01:52:18,817 --> 01:52:19,784
What...?

985
01:52:20,819 --> 01:52:21,786
And what do you think?

986
01:52:22,821 --> 01:52:24,789
That you will give me the resignation
and l will let you go?

987
01:52:29,828 --> 01:52:31,796
God has brought us together
at the right time

988
01:52:33,832 --> 01:52:35,800
You're lonely. So am l
Where would we meet, if not here?

989
01:52:37,836 --> 01:52:39,804
Why don't we get to know
each other better?

990
01:52:42,841 --> 01:52:43,808
You don't know anything about me

991
01:52:45,844 --> 01:52:47,812
l don't even want to

992
01:52:48,847 --> 01:52:50,815
That you've heard me out and haven't
even slapped me, is enough for me

993
01:52:54,853 --> 01:52:56,821
You look so nice when you smile.
Always keep smiling

994
01:53:00,859 --> 01:53:01,826
Wrong timing

995
01:53:04,863 --> 01:53:06,831
Whenever l'm going to say something
nice, Mr Chopra will always call up

996
01:53:10,869 --> 01:53:12,837
Mr Chopra? Yes, everything
has been arranged

997
01:53:14,873 --> 01:53:15,840
Yes, l've done my packing

998
01:53:16,875 --> 01:53:17,842
Aren't we going to Australia?
So...?

999
01:53:26,885 --> 01:53:28,853
l have a request.
Book another ticket

1000
01:53:30,889 --> 01:53:31,856
The name is... Pooja.
- No

1001
01:53:34,893 --> 01:53:35,860
lt's confirmed, yes

1002
01:53:38,897 --> 01:53:39,864
How can l...?

1003
01:53:42,901 --> 01:53:44,869
l've been all over the world.
But there's no place like Switzerland

1004
01:53:48,907 --> 01:53:49,874
lt's heaven!

1005
01:54:00,919 --> 01:54:02,887
Why don't you want to go, Pooja?
What's wrong with that?

1006
01:54:06,925 --> 01:54:08,893
Besides, you're going there
on business too

1007
01:54:10,929 --> 01:54:12,897
How long will you keep
feeling afraid like this?

1008
01:54:14,933 --> 01:54:16,901
How long will you cling
to your old memories?

1009
01:54:18,937 --> 01:54:19,904
How long will you hide?

1010
01:54:21,940 --> 01:54:23,908
You must set out
on the same path again

1011
01:54:24,943 --> 01:54:26,911
On the same path, you must wipe out
the old foot-prints with new ones

1012
01:54:35,954 --> 01:54:36,921
You must show courage, Pooja.
And move forward

1013
01:54:39,958 --> 01:54:40,925
Don't stop yourself. Don't

1014
01:54:43,962 --> 01:54:44,929
Life's once again calling out to you

1015
01:54:47,966 --> 01:54:49,934
You must embark a new journey
once again, Pooja

1016
01:54:54,973 --> 01:54:56,941
You must go, Pooja.
You must

1017
01:55:45,023 --> 01:55:45,990
There's that lady sitting
there on Seat No. 3B

1018
01:55:47,025 --> 01:55:48,993
Ask her what she wants.
Or she won't ask for anything

1019
01:55:59,037 --> 01:56:00,004
Thanks, l want nothing

1020
01:56:05,043 --> 01:56:07,011
Shiv! Leave me alone!
What are you doing?

1021
01:56:12,050 --> 01:56:14,018
This isn't our bedroom.
lt's an aircraft. Leave me alone!

1022
01:56:16,054 --> 01:56:17,021
You won't stop being mischievous!

1023
01:56:21,059 --> 01:56:22,026
Let me go...
- Should l?

1024
01:56:26,064 --> 01:56:28,032
Here goes. l'll be back in a moment?
- Where to? Come back soon

1025
01:56:41,079 --> 01:56:42,046
You've just been married?

1026
01:56:44,082 --> 01:56:46,050
Yes. A few days ago. We're going
to Switzerland on a honeymoon

1027
01:56:49,087 --> 01:56:50,054
The dream of every lndian

1028
01:56:51,089 --> 01:56:52,056
Right

1029
01:56:59,097 --> 01:57:00,064
ls this your first visit?
- No...

1030
01:57:05,103 --> 01:57:06,070
Yes. This is my first visit too

1031
01:57:07,105 --> 01:57:08,072
l'm told it's heaven

1032
01:57:11,109 --> 01:57:13,077
We could have gone anywhere
else in the world

1033
01:57:15,113 --> 01:57:17,081
But l believe that Switzerland
is very lucky for married couples

1034
01:57:19,117 --> 01:57:20,084
lt's just great for those in love

1035
01:57:25,123 --> 01:57:27,091
l'm very lucky. My husband
is a very nice man

1036
01:57:34,132 --> 01:57:35,099
Are you married?

1037
01:57:38,136 --> 01:57:39,103
No

1038
01:57:40,138 --> 01:57:42,106
Maybe you won't get the
same feeling as l do

1039
01:57:44,142 --> 01:57:46,110
From what l'm told,
it's a place...

1040
01:57:48,146 --> 01:57:49,113
which gives you memories
for a lifetime,...

1041
01:57:50,148 --> 01:57:52,116
should you spend a few moments
there with your beloved

1042
01:57:54,152 --> 01:57:56,120
No matter how much you try,
you can never erase those memories

1043
01:59:17,235 --> 01:59:19,203
''l'm your love;
my heart beats for you...''

1044
01:59:23,241 --> 01:59:24,208
''do always be with me''

1045
01:59:29,247 --> 01:59:31,215
''Should you have a grouse
against me...''

1046
01:59:36,254 --> 01:59:37,221
''do tell me''

1047
01:59:41,259 --> 01:59:42,226
''l have loved you too...''

1048
01:59:47,265 --> 01:59:48,232
''Yes, l have been in love too''

1049
01:59:54,272 --> 01:59:56,240
''l'm your love;
my heart beats for you...''

1050
02:00:01,279 --> 02:00:02,246
''do always be with me''

1051
02:00:06,284 --> 02:00:09,253
''Should you have a grouse
against me...''

1052
02:00:13,291 --> 02:00:14,258
''do tell me''

1053
02:00:16,294 --> 02:00:17,261
''But do be with me''

1054
02:00:20,298 --> 02:00:21,265
''l have loved you too...''

1055
02:00:25,303 --> 02:00:26,270
''Yes, l'm in love with you''

1056
02:01:43,381 --> 02:01:45,349
''How will l forget
the moments l spent?''

1057
02:01:50,388 --> 02:01:52,356
''Every moment,
those memories torment me''

1058
02:01:56,394 --> 02:01:58,362
''How will l tell you?
lt's a secret l keep with difficulty''

1059
02:02:01,399 --> 02:02:02,366
''Those moments never come...''

1060
02:02:05,403 --> 02:02:06,370
''what's true is here,
this moment''

1061
02:02:21,419 --> 02:02:23,387
''Come to me, my love.
Give me a smile and talk to me...''

1062
02:02:27,425 --> 02:02:28,392
''do not remain silent''

1063
02:02:40,438 --> 02:02:41,405
''do tell me''

1064
02:02:42,440 --> 02:02:43,407
''But do be with me''

1065
02:03:45,503 --> 02:03:46,470
''everything here is
for you, my love''

1066
02:03:52,510 --> 02:03:54,478
''There are thorns among roses,
and a chill in the snow''

1067
02:03:58,516 --> 02:04:00,484
''What fire consumes
my breath all day and night?''

1068
02:04:16,534 --> 02:04:17,501
''This cold breeze say...''

1069
02:04:24,542 --> 02:04:25,509
''do not burn thus''

1070
02:04:29,547 --> 02:04:31,515
''Should you have a grouse
against me...''

1071
02:04:36,554 --> 02:04:37,521
''do tell me''

1072
02:04:39,557 --> 02:04:40,524
''But do be with me''

1073
02:05:07,585 --> 02:05:08,552
''Yes, l am in love with you''

1074
02:05:21,599 --> 02:05:23,567
Here you are, Babban Miyan. The
clothes for your schedule are ready

1075
02:05:25,603 --> 02:05:27,571
Thank you very much.
- No, l must thank you

1076
02:05:33,611 --> 02:05:34,578
You gave Pooja such a nice job.
- We do nothing

1077
02:05:35,613 --> 02:05:37,581
God gives everyone
his rightful place

1078
02:05:42,620 --> 02:05:44,588
Not just a family member...
a lifetime member

1079
02:05:45,623 --> 02:05:47,591
What did l say the other day...?
- Shut up, Chinni

1080
02:05:50,628 --> 02:05:51,595
''Come unto me, O beloved''

1081
02:05:59,637 --> 02:06:01,605
Neha, everything is all right.
Just don't worry

1082
02:06:04,642 --> 02:06:05,609
Your boss always advises me
to wear ordinary clothes

1083
02:06:17,655 --> 02:06:19,623
Ordinary clothes give one
peace of mind

1084
02:06:23,661 --> 02:06:24,628
The heart is no longer restless

1085
02:06:27,665 --> 02:06:29,633
What is more, one has control
over his tongue

1086
02:06:32,670 --> 02:06:33,637
You folks...? Pranaam.
- Pranaam

1087
02:06:37,675 --> 02:06:38,642
How are you?

1088
02:06:39,677 --> 02:06:41,645
How's your lovely world
of films doing?

1089
02:06:43,681 --> 02:06:45,649
You make such lovely films

1090
02:06:46,684 --> 02:06:48,652
You are such lovely folks.
Aren't you?

1091
02:06:50,688 --> 02:06:52,656
Are you shooting a song again?
- Well...

1092
02:06:56,694 --> 02:06:57,661
Go ahead.
Make a whole lot of costumes

1093
02:07:01,699 --> 02:07:03,667
Change as many clothes
as you wish to

1094
02:07:07,705 --> 02:07:09,673
Behind trees, on the mountains...
change wherever you wish to

1095
02:07:14,712 --> 02:07:16,680
What have l to do with it?
Right?

1096
02:07:17,715 --> 02:07:19,683
Well, may Chana Singh,
wife of Ghana Singh, leave now?

1097
02:07:24,722 --> 02:07:26,690
My two children must be impatiently
waiting for their mother's arrival

1098
02:07:27,725 --> 02:07:30,694
Gana Singh must be waiting for me
at the religious gathering

1099
02:07:34,732 --> 02:07:35,699
''When will you come?''

1100
02:07:38,736 --> 02:07:40,704
Good bye.
- Good bye

1101
02:07:43,741 --> 02:07:44,708
''Come unto me, O beloved''

1102
02:08:08,766 --> 02:08:10,734
Gana's going to die!
What sorrow after happiness!

1103
02:08:15,773 --> 02:08:18,742
Pooja told me you're going to a hill
station for shooting, Babban Miyan

1104
02:08:23,781 --> 02:08:24,748
A beautiful hill station in lndia

1105
02:08:25,783 --> 02:08:26,750
Whenever we have been there,
something has always blossomed

1106
02:08:27,785 --> 02:08:29,753
Let's see what blossoms
at Naini Hills this time

1107
02:09:00,818 --> 02:09:02,786
''Tie the dancing-bells
to my feet...''

1108
02:09:07,825 --> 02:09:08,792
''and watch my swagger''

1109
02:09:20,838 --> 02:09:22,806
Oh yes. You're shooting at
Naini Hills this time

1110
02:09:24,842 --> 02:09:25,809
Where is the manager?

1111
02:09:26,844 --> 02:09:27,811
What for, sir?
What is it regarding?

1112
02:09:28,846 --> 02:09:30,814
Regarding? l've got to discuss
things with him. ln detail

1113
02:09:36,854 --> 02:09:38,822
His cabin is over there, sir

1114
02:09:45,863 --> 02:09:46,830
Manager, salutations

1115
02:09:54,872 --> 02:09:55,839
Greetings. Well?

1116
02:09:57,875 --> 02:09:59,843
l'm Mr Raj Malhotra's trusted man.
His driver, his Man Friday, Babban

1117
02:10:08,886 --> 02:10:10,854
l came to enquire about his room.
lt's secluded, l hope?

1118
02:10:12,890 --> 02:10:14,858
What does that mean?
- By God...

1119
02:10:16,894 --> 02:10:18,862
fans nowadays harass him a lot.
He's such a simple man...

1120
02:10:22,900 --> 02:10:24,868
he doesn't want the hassle.
- Don't worry

1121
02:10:27,905 --> 02:10:28,872
l've personally made all the
arrangements for him

1122
02:10:29,907 --> 02:10:31,875
You will have no cause for complaint.
- That's very kind of you. Thank you

1123
02:10:33,911 --> 02:10:35,879
You must have seen his films?
- No, l don't see films

1124
02:10:41,919 --> 02:10:43,887
You live in lndia and
don't watch films?

1125
02:10:46,924 --> 02:10:47,891
What say, manager...?
You're different too?

1126
02:10:52,930 --> 02:10:54,898
That's not how it is. l used to
see films earlier. l don't anymore

1127
02:10:57,935 --> 02:11:00,904
And you're missing nothing. Where are
the films they used to make earlier?

1128
02:11:06,944 --> 02:11:07,911
Where are those heroes
and heroines anymore?

1129
02:11:11,949 --> 02:11:12,916
Where will you find those stories?

1130
02:11:14,952 --> 02:11:15,919
What films they used to make

1131
02:11:17,955 --> 02:11:19,923
l used to be in Mr Yusuf Khan's
employ during those days

1132
02:11:20,958 --> 02:11:23,927
An artist like him has never graced
the lndian screen ever again

1133
02:11:26,964 --> 02:11:27,931
lt's all over.
After l left him...

1134
02:11:28,966 --> 02:11:30,934
l joined the hero.
My hero does only hit films

1135
02:11:35,973 --> 02:11:36,940
l make the choice

1136
02:11:38,976 --> 02:11:39,943
Which is why l'm with him

1137
02:11:41,979 --> 02:11:43,947
Even to take a look at his room,
this servant comes first...

1138
02:11:45,983 --> 02:11:46,950
he'll come later

1139
02:11:48,986 --> 02:11:50,954
Rest assured, Babban Miyan.
You will have no complaints

1140
02:11:54,992 --> 02:11:55,959
When is your boss arriving?

1141
02:11:58,996 --> 02:11:59,963
The hero's caravan should be here
any moment

1142
02:13:48,103 --> 02:13:51,072
Mr Raj Malhotra has checked in, sir.
You wanted to meet him, didn't you?

1143
02:13:58,113 --> 02:13:59,080
l'll talk to him over the phone.
Go on

1144
02:14:42,157 --> 02:14:43,124
May l speak to Mr Raj Malhotra?

1145
02:14:53,168 --> 02:14:54,135
Who's this?

1146
02:14:58,173 --> 02:14:59,140
The manager of this hotel

1147
02:15:02,177 --> 02:15:03,144
One moment

1148
02:15:06,181 --> 02:15:07,148
Call for you.
- Who is it?

1149
02:15:09,184 --> 02:15:10,151
The manager of this hotel.

1150
02:15:22,197 --> 02:15:23,164
My name is Shiv Kapoor

1151
02:15:27,202 --> 02:15:28,169
Yes, Manager?

1152
02:15:33,208 --> 02:15:35,176
lf there's anything you need,
please do let me know

1153
02:15:37,212 --> 02:15:38,179
You have a beautiful hotel

1154
02:15:41,216 --> 02:15:43,184
l can see in everything that
it's being managed nicely

1155
02:15:48,223 --> 02:15:50,191
lf there's anything you need,
you'll find me on extension 16

1156
02:15:52,227 --> 02:15:54,195
Please do call me.
- Of course l'll call you...

1157
02:15:55,230 --> 02:15:57,198
if l have problem.
Where else will l go?

1158
02:16:07,242 --> 02:16:09,210
But l'm finding everything
nice today

1159
02:16:12,247 --> 02:16:13,214
l'm the same,
so is everything else

1160
02:16:14,249 --> 02:16:15,216
Yet, l see a change
in something around

1161
02:16:16,251 --> 02:16:18,219
These eyes of mine have always
dreamt dreams for others, Pooja

1162
02:16:19,254 --> 02:16:21,222
For the first time, they're
daring to dream for themselves

1163
02:16:26,261 --> 02:16:28,229
They aren't doing anything
wrong, are they?

1164
02:16:33,268 --> 02:16:35,236
You can't ignore my remark
with a smile

1165
02:16:39,274 --> 02:16:40,241
You must give me an answer

1166
02:16:45,280 --> 02:16:48,249
You want to tell me something
before telling me about your decision?

1167
02:16:57,292 --> 02:16:59,260
You want to tell me
about your past?

1168
02:17:02,297 --> 02:17:03,264
l don't want to listen

1169
02:17:06,301 --> 02:17:07,268
But if it's going to relieve you
of a burden...

1170
02:17:10,305 --> 02:17:12,273
and makes it easier for you
to decide about me...

1171
02:17:16,311 --> 02:17:18,279
But remember this much.
No matter what you say...

1172
02:17:21,316 --> 02:17:22,283
my decision won't change

1173
02:17:26,321 --> 02:17:27,288
Speak

1174
02:17:29,324 --> 02:17:30,291
Speak, Pooja

1175
02:17:32,327 --> 02:17:33,294
l'm a divorcee

1176
02:17:37,332 --> 02:17:38,299
l was in love with someone

1177
02:17:41,336 --> 02:17:42,303
And we were separated

1178
02:17:47,342 --> 02:17:48,309
l told you, it won't
make a difference to me

1179
02:17:49,344 --> 02:17:51,312
lt'll stop making a difference to you
if you stop living in the past

1180
02:17:54,349 --> 02:17:55,316
Forget what has happened

1181
02:17:56,351 --> 02:17:58,319
What is with you now
is the only truth

1182
02:17:59,354 --> 02:18:01,322
So tell me quickly...
is it ''yes'' Or is it ''yes'' ?

1183
02:18:02,357 --> 02:18:04,325
Because there's no question
of saying ''No''

1184
02:18:08,363 --> 02:18:11,332
Know what? l'll pack up with
the shooting quickly...

1185
02:18:12,367 --> 02:18:14,335
and we'll go and prepare
for the wedding

1186
02:18:15,370 --> 02:18:17,338
No, that's wrong. We'll leave
after we complete our work

1187
02:18:20,375 --> 02:18:23,344
Get ready quickly. The whole unit
must be waiting there for you

1188
02:18:25,380 --> 02:18:27,348
l'll complete my pending work
and get there too

1189
02:18:44,399 --> 02:18:47,368
Let's have a small party in the
lawns of the hotel this evening

1190
02:18:48,403 --> 02:18:50,371
To celebrate our happiness
We won't tell anyone anything

1191
02:18:53,408 --> 02:18:55,376
Meet the manager and
organise the party

1192
02:18:56,411 --> 02:18:58,379
Now what was the manager's name...?

1193
02:20:08,483 --> 02:20:11,452
You're with Mr Raj Malhotra.
- That's right

1194
02:20:13,488 --> 02:20:15,456
Mr Malhotra wants to throw a small
party on the lawns tonight

1195
02:20:17,492 --> 02:20:18,459
l wanted to talk to you
about it

1196
02:20:19,494 --> 02:20:20,461
l want everything to
be perfectly organised

1197
02:20:23,498 --> 02:20:25,466
lt would be better if you could
discuss it with our manager

1198
02:20:27,502 --> 02:20:29,470
No. lt's enough that
l have spoken to you

1199
02:20:32,507 --> 02:20:34,475
Who is your manager, by the way?
- Mr Kapoor

1200
02:20:39,514 --> 02:20:41,482
His full name?
- Mr Shiv Kapoor

1201
02:20:46,521 --> 02:20:48,489
Has he just arrived?
- Yes. He's been with us for a year

1202
02:20:53,528 --> 02:20:54,495
Where is he from?
- Delhi

1203
02:20:58,533 --> 02:21:01,502
Where does he stay here?
- ln the cottage behind the hotel

1204
02:21:04,539 --> 02:21:06,507
ls his family here too?
- No, he's all alone

1205
02:21:10,545 --> 02:21:12,513
l see. Please see that everything
is perfectly organised

1206
02:21:42,577 --> 02:21:44,545
He's the manager you were
asking me about, madam

1207
02:21:50,585 --> 02:21:52,553
She was asking me so many
questions about you...

1208
02:21:55,590 --> 02:21:57,558
and she just walks away now.
Strange!

1209
02:22:08,603 --> 02:22:09,570
''What's love...?''

1210
02:22:12,607 --> 02:22:13,574
''fall in love,
and you will know''

1211
02:22:14,609 --> 02:22:15,576
''Make her laugh some,
make her cry some''

1212
02:22:18,613 --> 02:22:20,581
''The firefly burns...
and why?''

1213
02:22:27,622 --> 02:22:29,590
''burn yourself,
if you must discover the secret''

1214
02:22:32,627 --> 02:22:34,595
Heroji, you're playing
the firefly today...

1215
02:22:37,632 --> 02:22:39,600
and where is your flame?
- Keep that under wraps

1216
02:22:42,637 --> 02:22:44,605
''Why ask him about
playing Romeo''

1217
02:22:46,641 --> 02:22:47,608
''Come to me,
thou shall be Juliet''

1218
02:22:48,643 --> 02:22:49,610
That's great, Babban Miyan!

1219
02:22:52,647 --> 02:22:53,614
What's happening?

1220
02:22:59,654 --> 02:23:00,621
Everybody disappears
in the darkness?

1221
02:23:04,659 --> 02:23:05,626
Where's everybody?

1222
02:23:14,669 --> 02:23:15,636
Who are you?

1223
02:23:18,673 --> 02:23:19,640
l'm the manager of this hotel

1224
02:23:21,676 --> 02:23:23,644
There's a power-failure.
lt'll be restored soon

1225
02:23:25,680 --> 02:23:26,647
So you are the manager?

1226
02:23:30,685 --> 02:23:32,653
l must say, you've done
a great job of our party

1227
02:23:34,689 --> 02:23:35,656
You remember my name?

1228
02:23:36,691 --> 02:23:38,659
Once l hear a name,
l don't ever forget it

1229
02:23:39,694 --> 02:23:41,662
And you have such a lovely name.
Shiv Kapoor

1230
02:23:43,698 --> 02:23:45,666
l'm thinking of using that name
for myself in my next film

1231
02:23:49,704 --> 02:23:51,672
You appear to be very happy, sir.
You've even thrown a party

1232
02:23:53,708 --> 02:23:55,676
What makes you so happy?
- That's just what l can't tell you

1233
02:23:57,712 --> 02:23:59,680
lt's giving me a stomach-ache!
But l think l'll tell you how l feel

1234
02:24:05,720 --> 02:24:06,687
l'll at least be rid
of the stomach-ache

1235
02:24:07,722 --> 02:24:08,689
Must l...?
- Go ahead, sir

1236
02:24:09,724 --> 02:24:11,692
lf it will relieve you of your
stomach-ache, give me the pain sir

1237
02:24:14,729 --> 02:24:16,697
You won't tell anyone, will you?

1238
02:24:18,733 --> 02:24:19,700
Sure?

1239
02:24:23,738 --> 02:24:24,705
l've fallen in love with someone

1240
02:24:26,741 --> 02:24:28,709
And l'm going to get married
the moment l leave this place

1241
02:24:29,744 --> 02:24:30,711
Congratulations. Who is it?

1242
02:24:35,750 --> 02:24:36,717
The lights are back!

1243
02:24:40,755 --> 02:24:41,722
And my beloved too

1244
02:24:54,769 --> 02:24:56,737
Pooja, you must've met him already.
The manager, Mr Shiv Kapoor

1245
02:24:58,773 --> 02:24:59,740
Look at the pains he has taken
to make this a grand party

1246
02:25:00,775 --> 02:25:01,742
He's amazing

1247
02:25:05,780 --> 02:25:07,748
Why don't we let him handle
the decorations at our wedding?

1248
02:25:10,785 --> 02:25:12,753
l don't know why, but l felt
a sense of belonging with him

1249
02:25:14,789 --> 02:25:15,756
And l told him my secret

1250
02:25:17,792 --> 02:25:19,760
We have decided that you will handle
the decorations at our wedding

1251
02:25:20,795 --> 02:25:21,762
Well?
- Yes

1252
02:25:23,798 --> 02:25:24,765
You will make it as beautiful
as this party. You are amazing!

1253
02:25:25,800 --> 02:25:27,768
You get married only
once in a lifetime

1254
02:25:28,803 --> 02:25:30,771
l want my wedding to be
such a grand affair...

1255
02:25:32,807 --> 02:25:34,775
that people are left stunned.
Let's shake hands. C'mon!

1256
02:25:42,817 --> 02:25:44,785
Raj, are you through
with your couplets?

1257
02:25:45,820 --> 02:25:46,787
There's a gathering there also.
Let's go

1258
02:25:47,822 --> 02:25:49,790
l'll recite a couplet
and be back. lt's just that...

1259
02:25:54,829 --> 02:25:56,797
''lf there is anything that
is ignorant, it's the rose''

1260
02:25:57,832 --> 02:25:58,799
''The whole garden
knows the secret''

1261
02:26:01,836 --> 02:26:03,804
Pooja, l want to discuss
something with you

1262
02:26:04,839 --> 02:26:06,807
But l don't wish to talk to you

1263
02:26:10,845 --> 02:26:11,812
l'll wait for you in my cottage

1264
02:26:56,891 --> 02:26:57,858
Will you remain standing there?

1265
02:26:59,894 --> 02:27:00,861
Come on in

1266
02:27:20,915 --> 02:27:21,882
Sit down

1267
02:27:22,917 --> 02:27:24,885
Won't you sit?
- No. l'm okay

1268
02:27:29,924 --> 02:27:30,891
You're still angry?

1269
02:27:34,929 --> 02:27:35,896
You're still sulking?

1270
02:27:41,936 --> 02:27:43,904
You haven't changed.
Not in the least

1271
02:27:48,943 --> 02:27:50,911
You're still the same person
l first met

1272
02:27:54,949 --> 02:27:56,917
When you and l fought
for the same job

1273
02:27:59,954 --> 02:28:00,921
And we're still fighting

1274
02:28:08,963 --> 02:28:10,931
Know something, Pooja?
l could never get over the fact...

1275
02:28:15,970 --> 02:28:17,938
that you gave up everything you had
in just a moment. Only for me

1276
02:28:22,977 --> 02:28:23,944
To settle down with me

1277
02:28:27,982 --> 02:28:28,949
You came to be my companion

1278
02:28:37,992 --> 02:28:39,960
l don't know if you
ever miss me, Pooja...

1279
02:28:48,002 --> 02:28:48,969
but l could never forget you

1280
02:28:53,007 --> 02:28:53,974
Never

1281
02:28:58,012 --> 02:28:59,980
To forget you, l left that job,
that city and all those memories...

1282
02:29:07,021 --> 02:29:07,988
and started living here

1283
02:29:14,028 --> 02:29:14,995
But you have come here too

1284
02:29:20,034 --> 02:29:22,002
Just as destiny always brought us
together...

1285
02:29:25,039 --> 02:29:27,007
it's the same destiny that
has brought us together again

1286
02:29:32,046 --> 02:29:34,014
When l found you asking about me,
it gave me a lot of confidence

1287
02:29:38,052 --> 02:29:40,020
l thought you had not been
able to forget me

1288
02:29:44,058 --> 02:29:45,025
So why all this, Pooja?

1289
02:29:48,062 --> 02:29:50,030
How can you leave me
and go ahead like this?

1290
02:29:53,067 --> 02:29:55,035
lt's my free will. Who are you
to ask me why l'm doing all this?

1291
02:29:59,073 --> 02:30:00,040
l will do as l please

1292
02:30:01,075 --> 02:30:02,042
l do not need to seek
permission from anyone

1293
02:30:03,077 --> 02:30:05,045
And l've seen what l got
when l asked earlier

1294
02:30:08,082 --> 02:30:09,049
Deceit! And betrayal!

1295
02:30:15,089 --> 02:30:16,056
Pooja, can't you forget all that?

1296
02:30:24,098 --> 02:30:26,066
Must you give me such a big punishment
for something so trivial?

1297
02:30:28,102 --> 02:30:29,069
So trivial? You call it trivial?

1298
02:30:34,108 --> 02:30:36,076
What didn't l do for you?
l changed the course of my life!

1299
02:30:40,114 --> 02:30:41,081
When a woman gives up everything
for her man...

1300
02:30:43,117 --> 02:30:45,085
she nurtures the relationship with
sincerity, devotion and desires

1301
02:30:48,122 --> 02:30:50,090
l honoured every vow
l took with you

1302
02:30:52,126 --> 02:30:54,094
But you forgot the vow of fidelity
you had taken with me

1303
02:30:56,130 --> 02:30:58,098
You had sworn to remain loyal,
you had sworn to be faithful

1304
02:31:00,134 --> 02:31:02,102
By breaking the sacred vows,
you have deceived not only me...

1305
02:31:03,137 --> 02:31:05,105
you have betrayed God too!
You are a sinner!

1306
02:31:07,141 --> 02:31:08,108
And you must be punished
for your sins!

1307
02:31:10,144 --> 02:31:11,111
Really? So what do you want?

1308
02:31:12,146 --> 02:31:14,114
What punishment do you
want to give me?

1309
02:31:18,152 --> 02:31:19,119
Do you want me to be hanged?

1310
02:31:23,157 --> 02:31:24,124
l admit, l have made
a mistake Pooja

1311
02:31:25,159 --> 02:31:26,126
But my home was shattered too

1312
02:31:28,162 --> 02:31:30,130
You gave me a divorce and
severed your relationship with me

1313
02:31:31,165 --> 02:31:33,133
But you didn't give me even one
opportunity to explain

1314
02:31:37,171 --> 02:31:38,138
l didn't say a word then, Pooja...

1315
02:31:40,174 --> 02:31:41,141
because l thought
you were very angry

1316
02:31:43,177 --> 02:31:44,144
And your anger was justified

1317
02:31:46,180 --> 02:31:48,148
But you're still as angry
and obstinate as ever

1318
02:31:54,188 --> 02:31:56,156
You have no place for me
in your heart

1319
02:31:58,192 --> 02:32:00,160
One mistake, even God forgives

1320
02:32:01,195 --> 02:32:03,163
So go and seek forgiveness from God!
l can't forgive you. Never!

1321
02:32:05,199 --> 02:32:06,166
l can't forgive you. l can't.
Never

1322
02:32:30,224 --> 02:32:31,191
All right, Pooja

1323
02:32:37,231 --> 02:32:39,199
lf this is what you want,
l will not come in your way

1324
02:32:45,239 --> 02:32:47,207
l will not come between
the two of you

1325
02:32:52,246 --> 02:32:53,213
l think l must leave
this place

1326
02:32:58,252 --> 02:32:59,219
But l have promised the man
you're going to marry...

1327
02:33:03,257 --> 02:33:05,225
that l will decorate his wedding

1328
02:33:08,262 --> 02:33:09,229
You will no problems from me
during this wedding

1329
02:33:17,271 --> 02:33:19,239
Believe me or not...

1330
02:33:22,276 --> 02:33:24,244
from my heart will come
the best wishes for you

1331
02:33:27,281 --> 02:33:28,248
From my heart

1332
02:33:59,313 --> 02:34:00,280
Come on, guys

1333
02:34:27,341 --> 02:34:29,309
Why the tension, Mr Khanna?
- l have a problem, Raj

1334
02:34:32,346 --> 02:34:34,314
The guy who was supposed
to sing at your wedding,...

1335
02:34:35,349 --> 02:34:36,316
his flight has been cancelled

1336
02:34:37,351 --> 02:34:38,318
You're the only one who can
do something now. Save my skin!

1337
02:34:39,353 --> 02:34:40,320
You want me to sing?
- Yes

1338
02:34:42,356 --> 02:34:43,323
So everybody else runs away?
- Oh no

1339
02:34:46,360 --> 02:34:47,327
Ask one of the guests, producer

1340
02:34:50,364 --> 02:34:51,331
One of them must undoubtedly
have feeling in his voice

1341
02:34:53,367 --> 02:34:55,335
Why don't you sing, Sardarji?
- No! The bride will run away!

1342
02:35:00,374 --> 02:35:01,341
No, we don't want a song in Tamil

1343
02:35:06,380 --> 02:35:07,347
May l suggest something, Mr Raj?
- Go ahead

1344
02:35:08,382 --> 02:35:09,349
The manager has an amazing voice

1345
02:35:11,385 --> 02:35:12,352
lf his song doesn't make your
wedding greater, nothing will

1346
02:35:13,387 --> 02:35:14,354
Where is he?
- Who's that?

1347
02:35:18,392 --> 02:35:19,359
But where is he...?
Shiv saheb!

1348
02:35:24,398 --> 02:35:25,365
Here he is

1349
02:35:27,401 --> 02:35:28,368
Yes? ls everything okay?

1350
02:35:31,405 --> 02:35:32,372
Yes, everything is okay, but...

1351
02:35:35,409 --> 02:35:36,376
your secrets are being exposed

1352
02:35:41,415 --> 02:35:42,382
Pardon me?

1353
02:35:45,419 --> 02:35:47,387
You deserve praise for doing
a great job with my wedding

1354
02:35:49,423 --> 02:35:51,391
You have done me a great favour.
So please do me another

1355
02:35:53,427 --> 02:35:54,394
What?
- l'm told you have a great voice

1356
02:35:59,433 --> 02:36:01,401
The guy who was to be here to sing
won't be coming

1357
02:36:03,437 --> 02:36:05,405
So please sing something.
Something...

1358
02:36:06,440 --> 02:36:08,408
that will make me, my guests
and my bride... just sway!

1359
02:36:11,445 --> 02:36:12,412
We must remember nothing
except you!

1360
02:36:15,449 --> 02:36:16,416
What? Me?

1361
02:36:19,453 --> 02:36:21,421
Yes, you. Know what they call someone
who stands by you in such times?

1362
02:36:25,459 --> 02:36:26,426
The best friend. The friend...

1363
02:36:31,465 --> 02:36:32,432
who gives the bride away
to the bridegroom

1364
02:36:40,474 --> 02:36:42,442
Forget it. Sing something that
makes your voice a blessing for us

1365
02:36:49,483 --> 02:36:50,450
Please sing

1366
02:36:59,493 --> 02:37:01,461
''May the vermillion on your forehead
forever shine''

1367
02:37:24,518 --> 02:37:25,485
''May the henna on your palms,
forever be fragrant''

1368
02:37:26,520 --> 02:37:27,487
''May you forever be together''

1369
02:37:35,529 --> 02:37:37,497
''May your bangles
forever tinkle''

1370
02:37:56,550 --> 02:37:57,517
''Bless you, bless you''

1371
02:38:08,562 --> 02:38:09,529
''May your wedding be blessed''

1372
02:38:23,577 --> 02:38:25,545
''May you always be happy.
l pray for you''

1373
02:38:31,585 --> 02:38:33,553
''May the world kiss the earth
you tread on...''

1374
02:38:45,599 --> 02:38:47,567
''may you always be happy.
l pray for you''

1375
02:39:33,647 --> 02:39:34,614
''For you is the Spring''

1376
02:39:41,655 --> 02:39:42,622
''May you never face any sorrow''

1377
02:39:48,662 --> 02:39:49,629
''What is it about me?
l'm crazy''

1378
02:39:57,671 --> 02:39:58,638
''Nobody knows how l suffer''

1379
02:40:03,677 --> 02:40:04,644
''May you never have to
pine for love''

1380
02:40:18,692 --> 02:40:20,660
''May you always be happy.
l pray for you''

1381
02:41:24,758 --> 02:41:26,726
''Ties of a lifetime,
you can never sever''

1382
02:41:31,765 --> 02:41:32,732
''Midway through a journey,
you don't desert your companion''

1383
02:41:39,773 --> 02:41:40,740
''You mustn't ever forget
the norms''

1384
02:41:46,780 --> 02:41:47,747
''The vows you take, you must honour''

1385
02:41:53,787 --> 02:41:54,754
''l have spent a lifetime
in loneliness...''

1386
02:42:09,803 --> 02:42:11,771
''may you always be happy.
l pray for you''

1387
02:43:22,876 --> 02:43:23,843
''l have been in love too''

1388
02:43:32,886 --> 02:43:33,853
''Yes, l have also been in love''

1389
02:43:41,895 --> 02:43:42,862
''Yes, l have been in love''

1390
02:43:51,905 --> 02:43:52,872
''Yes, l have also been in love''

1391
02:44:19,933 --> 02:44:20,900
Pooja, come...
l'm here to take you along

1392
02:44:28,942 --> 02:44:30,910
The guests are waiting
for you downstairs

1393
02:44:34,948 --> 02:44:35,915
l have kept my promise

1394
02:44:39,953 --> 02:44:40,920
l have no complaints or regrets

1395
02:44:43,957 --> 02:44:44,924
l face no dilemma...
that you're leaving

1396
02:44:52,966 --> 02:44:54,934
Your bridegroom has sent me with
so much of love, to fetch you

1397
02:44:57,971 --> 02:44:58,938
As his best man.
As his best friend

1398
02:45:06,980 --> 02:45:08,948
Something like this must
never have happened before

1399
02:45:09,983 --> 02:45:11,951
Perhaps this is the
first time ever...

1400
02:45:15,989 --> 02:45:17,957
that a man is getting his wife
married to someone else

1401
02:45:30,003 --> 02:45:30,970
lt isn't a nice thing to happen

1402
02:45:34,007 --> 02:45:34,974
To punish you, l have punished myself

1403
02:45:39,012 --> 02:45:39,979
Why didn't l forgive you?

1404
02:45:43,016 --> 02:45:44,984
Despite the love l had for you...
why did l deny myself?

1405
02:45:50,023 --> 02:45:51,991
What am l to do, Shiv?
What am l to do?

1406
02:45:56,029 --> 02:45:57,997
The sacred fire around which
we took the vows...

1407
02:46:02,035 --> 02:46:04,003
now chars my heart! lt won't
let me erase your name

1408
02:46:07,040 --> 02:46:08,007
lt won't let your name
be erased

1409
02:46:15,048 --> 02:46:16,015
Pooja, Raj is waiting
for us downstairs

1410
02:46:25,058 --> 02:46:26,025
His guests are waiting for us.
We must go now

1411
02:46:29,062 --> 02:46:30,029
Come on

1412
02:47:10,103 --> 02:47:12,071
You knew Shiv and
didn't even tell me?

1413
02:47:20,113 --> 02:47:22,081
You knew each other...
and l didn't even get to know?

1414
02:47:29,122 --> 02:47:31,090
ls he the man you were married to?

1415
02:47:39,132 --> 02:47:41,100
ls he the man you have
never been able to forget?

1416
02:47:49,142 --> 02:47:51,110
So he's the one you loved
with all your heart

1417
02:47:58,151 --> 02:48:01,120
He's the one you wanted to punish,
and ended up punishing yourself

1418
02:48:17,170 --> 02:48:19,138
This story began between
the two of you

1419
02:48:22,175 --> 02:48:24,143
Will you decide its conclusion now?
Or must l do it?

1420
02:48:39,192 --> 02:48:41,160
l'm told it's difficult
for lovers to get together

1421
02:48:46,199 --> 02:48:48,167
As far as l know and feel...

1422
02:48:50,203 --> 02:48:52,171
l think the two of you
are made for each other

1423
02:48:56,209 --> 02:48:58,177
What is right and what is wrong,
what's true and what's not...

1424
02:49:04,217 --> 02:49:06,185
who ought to be punished,
who should be forgiven...?

1425
02:49:07,220 --> 02:49:09,188
mere mortals like us
can not decide

1426
02:49:11,224 --> 02:49:13,192
But yes, if there is anything
that can decide it...

1427
02:49:15,228 --> 02:49:16,195
it's the vows you take to remain
together for seven lifetimes

1428
02:49:20,233 --> 02:49:22,201
And every vow you take together.
Which you can't forget so easily

1429
02:49:30,243 --> 02:49:32,211
lt's true, Pooja. That's just why
you couldn't move any further

1430
02:49:36,249 --> 02:49:38,217
Your eyes could never see
the truth behind the norms

1431
02:49:42,255 --> 02:49:43,222
You can't love anyone but Shiv

1432
02:49:48,261 --> 02:49:50,229
Pooja, signatures on a piece of paper
don't make or break relationships

1433
02:49:56,269 --> 02:49:58,237
The name you write on your heart...

1434
02:49:59,272 --> 02:50:01,240
you can never erase
in a lifetime

1435
02:50:04,277 --> 02:50:06,245
And there's just one name
in your heart. Shiv's

1436
02:50:12,285 --> 02:50:13,252
When you severed your relationship...

1437
02:50:16,289 --> 02:50:18,257
there was no one to stop you
or reason with you

1438
02:50:22,295 --> 02:50:24,263
And see where it has taken
the two of you

1439
02:50:28,301 --> 02:50:30,269
Only the fortunate ones have
someone to lead you by hand

1440
02:50:36,309 --> 02:50:38,277
l'll show you the way
ou could never understand

1441
02:50:44,317 --> 02:50:46,285
l'll restore for good, this
relationship that had broken

1442
02:52:45,438 --> 02:52:47,406
l hope you had a comfortable stay
and a successful conference

1443
02:53:05,458 --> 02:53:06,425
What are you doing here?

1444
02:53:09,462 --> 02:53:11,430
You're the one who's surprising me!
lt's seven years since we last met

1445
02:53:14,467 --> 02:53:16,435
Seven years?

1446
02:53:19,472 --> 02:53:20,439
We studied together in college

1447
02:53:33,486 --> 02:53:35,454
He was always busy with
his studies and sports

1448
02:53:36,489 --> 02:53:38,457
Now that l see you, l realise that
he had a great eye for women

1449
02:53:40,493 --> 02:53:42,461
He reserved it for you

1450
02:53:53,506 --> 02:53:55,474
l'm here for a conference

1451
02:53:58,511 --> 02:53:59,478
You will eat, won't you?

1452
02:54:01,514 --> 02:54:02,481
Shall we go?

